\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The warning letters began arriving during the week before the first anniversary of the Grafton Street bombing. The first one was timed to reach Ireland too late for counteraction. Others went to world 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 leaders, where they were treated as crank letters or were bucked along to specialists. The letters were numerous at first \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 to radio and television news departments, to newspapers, to prime ministers and presidents and church leaders. It was determined la\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
er that one of the first letters was delivered to a newspaper editor on Dublin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Connell Street.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The editor, Alex Coleman, was a dark and vital man who covered his drive with a generally mild manner even when he was being most forceful. He was consi\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
dered an oddity among his peers because of his strong temperance beliefs, but none doubted his penetrating alertness to a good story.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Coleman read the letter several times, glancing up occasionally to look out his third-floor window onto the street, w\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 here Dublin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s morning traffic already had begun to congeal into its usual frustrating crawl.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Crank letter?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The thing didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t have that feeling about it. The warnings and threats made his skin crawl. Was this possible? The words had an educated air\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 about them, sophisticated. The thing was typed on bond paper. He rubbed the paper between his fingers. Expensive stuff.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Owney O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 More, Coleman\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s personal secretary, had clipped a note to the letter: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I hope this is a crank. Should we call the Garda?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      So it had worked its disturbance on Owney.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Once more, Coleman read through the letter, seeking some reason to disregard it. Presently, he put the letter flat in front of him and keyed the intercom to Owney.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sir?\'94\loch\f0  Owney\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice always had a \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 military abruptness.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Check out the Achill Island angle, will you, Owney? Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t stir up any hornets. Just find out if there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s anything unusual afoot.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Right away.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Coleman returned his attention to the letter. It was so damned direct, so cl\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ear and straightforward. A mind of power and\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 yes, terrifying purpose, lay behind it. There was the usual warning to publish \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 or else\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  but then\'85
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I am going to wreak an appropriate revenge upon all of Ireland, Great Britain and Libya.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The expres\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 sed justification rang a bell in Coleman\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s memory.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You have wronged me by killing my loved ones. By my hand alone you are being called to account. You murdered my Mary and our children, Kevin and Mairead. I have sworn a treble vow on their memories. 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I will be avenged in kind.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Coleman again keyed the intercom and asked Owney to check on those names. \'93\loch\f0 And while you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
re at it, call the College Hospital and see if you can get me through to Fin Doheny.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That would be Fintan Craig Doheny, sir?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0     \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Right.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Once more, Coleman read the letter. He was interrupted by the telephone and intercom simultaneously. Owney\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s voice said: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Doctor Doheny on the line, sir.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Coleman picked up the phone. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Fin?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s so all-fired important, Alex?\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  Owney O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 More sounds like he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s been scalded.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve a threatening letter, Fin. And there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s some technical stuff in it. Mind listening a minute?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Get on with it.\'94\loch\f0  Doheny\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice had an echo quality, suggesting a speaker phone.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Is someone el\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 se with you?\'94\loch\f0  Coleman asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 No. What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s got the wind up?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Coleman sighed and returned his attention to the letter, extracting the technical references for Doheny.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s hard to say from just a letter,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 But I find no fault with\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 his references to the recombinant DNA process. You know, Alex, it is possible that way to make new diseases\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  but this\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The threat could be real?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d give that a qualified yes.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Then I shouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t disregard this thing?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d be calli\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ng the Garda.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Is there anything else I should be doing?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Well, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll give that a think and be back to you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 One thing, Fin! Not a word on this until I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve had a go at it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Aw, you scramblin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  newspapermen!\'94\loch\f0  But there was a hint of lau\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ghter in Doheny\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s voice that Coleman found reassuring. A qualified yes. Doheny wasn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t too worried then. It was still a good story, though, Coleman thought as he replaced the telephone in its cradle. A bomb victim\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s vengeance. Medical expert says the thing\loch\af0\dbch\af11\hich\f0 \rquote \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 s possible.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Owney\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s voice came over the intercom: \'93\loch\f0 Sir, that bomb at Grafton and St. Stephen\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s Green. You remember that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That bloody thing!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Sir, three of the victims had the names in this letter. There was a Mary O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill killed with her \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 twin children, Kevin and Mairead.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 From America, yes, I remember.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The husband was at the window of a bank down the street and saw it all happen. Name of\'85\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Owney paused, then: \'93\loch\f0 Doctor John Roe O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
\hich\f0 Neill.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Medical?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 No, a professor of \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 some sort. He was here on one of those foundation grant things they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re so fond of \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 studying the state of genetics or some\'85\loch\f0  yes, that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s what our story says. Genetics research.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Genetics,\'94\loch\f0  Coleman mused.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 According to our story at the time, sir. \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 This O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill had something to do with physical chemistry \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  a biophysicist 
\hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  and he taught at some school of pharmacy in the States. Says here he also owned a pharmacy there.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Coleman suddenly shuddered. He felt that something evil had crawled beneath \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
the surface of his land, a thing more venomous than any snake the Sainted Patrick had banned. That IRA bomb could come to be known as the most awful mistake in human history.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Any luck getting through to Achill?\'94\loch\f0  Coleman asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 The lines are jam\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 med, sir. Should we dispatch an aircraft?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Not yet. Get on to the Garda. If the Achill phones are jammed, they may know something. Did you copy this letter?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Two copies, sir.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll want the original\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 If they don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t have one of th\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 eir own already.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I thought of that. I just don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t like tipping our hand. We may have a head start on this. Well, we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll just have to chance it.\'94\loch\f0 
\hich\f0  He glanced down at the letter on his desk. \'93\loch\f0 I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t suppose there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s any chance of getting fingerprints off\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  this, anyway.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Are we going ahead with the story, sir?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Owney, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 m almost afraid not to publish it. There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s something about it. And singling out Achill this way\'85\loch\f0  \hich\f0 \lquote 
\loch\f0 a demonstration,\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  he says.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Sir, you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve thought of the panic we might\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0   \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0    \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Just get me the Garda, Owney.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Right away, sir!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Coleman picked up his phone and called his wife at home, making it brief and imperative.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s going to be trouble over a story we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re about to publish,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he explained. \'93\loch\f0 I want you to ta
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ke the boys and go to your brother\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s in Madrid.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      When she started to protest, he cut her off: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 This is going to be bad\'85\loch\f0  I think. If you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re here, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 m vulnerable. Don\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 t waste any time; just leave. Call me from Madrid and I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll explain.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He replaced \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
the phone in its cradle, feeling somewhat foolish but relieved. Panic? If this thing proved to be true, there would be worse than panic. He stared at the letter, focusing on the signature.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The Madman.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Coleman shook his head slowly, recalling th\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e tale of the Irish coffin-ship survivor who, making a cross of shovels over his wife\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s grave at Grosse Isle, Quebec, had vowed: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 By the cross, Mary, I swear to avenge your death.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neil\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s wife had been named Mary. And now, if this was O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill, he ca\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 lled himself simply \'93\loch\f0 
\hich\f0 The Madman.\'94
