\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      On the day before the Achill Island quarantine, Stephen Browder and Kate O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 G\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ara drove off together to Lough Derg, planning to lunch near Killaloe and then drive on to a cottage on the lake near Cloonoon. It was to be a stolen three days together before examinations and a hectic summer schedule for Stephen, who now planned to spec
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 alize in high-pressure medicine.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The cottage, a remodeled farmhouse, belonged to Adrian Peard, who had graduated six years ahead of Stephen and already was recognized as an important researcher in pressure medicine and the ailments of divers. Peard, s
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
cion of a wealthy old County Cork family, had established a vacation and weekend base at the cottage on the lake, installing a large steel pressure-decompression tank in the barn behind the cottage. Stephen had been several times to the cottage, earning m
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ney as a guinea pig in Peard\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s experiments.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Since their first sexual experience beside the Mallow Road, Kate had rationed them to one or two repeats a month and then only at her least fertile times. She had resisted this outing at first because it coi
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ncided with her highest fertility period, but Stephen had promised to \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 be careful.\'94\loch\f0  Kate, not certain what that meant, had warned:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll not be having any bastards in our family, Stephen Browder!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They had arranged the outing with care. Kate ost\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ensibly was with her friend, Maggie, on a holiday in Dublin. Stephen supposedly was boating with friends near Kinsale.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Peard, who had guessed the nature of Stephen\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s involvement with Kate, had volunteered the use of his Lough Derg cottage \'93\loch\f0 when it doe\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 sn\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t interfere with my schedule.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He had handed over the keys with a laugh and the admonition: \'93\loch\f0 Leave the place neat and do try to get in a little time for study. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
d tike you with me someday, Stephen. You have a talent for solving unusual problems\'85\loch\f0  such \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 s this one.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      As Peard had expected, Stephen blushed \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  as much from the praise as from the conspiracy.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The car they took was a tiny green Fiat whose use Stephen had earned tutoring its owner in the niceties of kidney function, a subject that baffl\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ed the Fiat\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s owner until Stephen hit on the stratagem of a large drawing with signposts on pins through which the student was required to maneuver a tiny cardboard automobile labeled \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 foreign matter.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 It amused Stephen and Kate to call the Fiat \'93\loch\f0 foreign \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 m\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 atter\'94\loch\f0  as they drove north.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A few minutes before noon they crossed the narrow old stone bridge into Killaloe. The castellated tower of St. Flannery\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s Cathedral stood out like a Norman sentinel against a gathering of clouds on the horizon. The sky over\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
head was blue, however, and the lake was a blue-and-emerald mirror to the surrounding hills, its surface rippled by a light wind and the passage of a quartet of swans.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Just north of Killaloe, Stephen stopped at a roadside \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 gypsy stand\'94\loch\f0  for sandwiches,\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 chips and beer, which they ate in the meadow beside the mound where Brian Bora had raised his castle. Their picnic site looked down on Ballyvalle Ford where Patrick Sarsfield and his six hundred troopers had crossed the Shannon on the night of August 10,
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 1690, during the Siege of Limerick.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Kate, fascinated by her nation\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s history and a little awed to be \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 in this very place,\'94\loch\f0  began regaling Stephen with the story of Sarsfield\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 s ride when she found him unfamiliar with the details. Watching her color ris\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 e as she talked about that \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 wonderful, futile ride\'94\loch\f0 
 against the Williamite siege train, Stephen looked longingly at the concealing shade of the trees that hid the circular foundation of Brian Boru\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s castle, wondering if Kate might agree to walk into that 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
heltering bower with him for a time. But he could hear children shouting at the lake below the meadow, and the picnic site soon was buzzing with flies attracted by the food. They wolfed their food and ran back to the car, pursued by the flies.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      In the \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 shelter of the car, Kate looked back at the meadow and surprised Stephen with a mystical side of her nature that he had not suspected.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Terrible things were done in that place, Stephen. I can feel it. Could the flies be the souls of the evil men who d\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 id those terrible things?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Ahhh, now, Kate! What a thing to say.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      She did not really cheer up until they turned down the graveled track to the cottage and she saw the old double chimney pot above the trees. When they entered the cottage, she was\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
