\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The Team reconvened\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  after lunch that first day with its pattern well set \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 Beckett in charge, Lepikov simmeringly resentful, Godelinsky weaving intuitively through her maze of questions, Danzas reserved and watchful, Hupp darting like a terrier around every new idea, and Fo\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 s
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 s sitting there like an aloof goddess.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Hupp was amused that they chose the more intimate lighting for the room when they reconvened. It focused only on the long table, leaving the rest of the space in remote shadows.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The Team clustered loosely ne\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ar one end of the table with their notes and briefcases around them. The sparring between Danzas and Lepikov had become more subtle \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 a raised eyebrow, a gentle cough at an inappropriate moment. Danzas took to stacking and restacking his papers while Lepi\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 k\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ov spoke. Lepikov\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s animosity toward Foss had resolved itself into calflike hurt glances that avoided Foss\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s ample breasts. Godelinsky obviously had made the \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 sisters under the skin\'94\loch\f0 
 decision to side with Foss, a thing that galled Lepikov, but he came bac\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 k\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  to the meeting saying he had orders to follow Beckett\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s lead.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Preparing himself to speak at length on this, Lepikov pushed himself back in his chair at Beckett\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s right and stared across the table where Danzas was leafing through notes with a noisy ru
