\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Surely, Mister President,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  the secretary-general said, \'93\loch\f0 some way could b\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e found to save what\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s left of your DIC team. They seem to be so remarkably well met.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The secretary-general, Huls Anders Bergen, was a Norwegian educated in England. He had played a number of golf games with the man on the telephone and, on those occ\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
asions, they had been Hab and Adam. But Adam Prescott was firmly seated in his office as President of the United States today. There was no camaraderie in his voice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      What is troubling him besides the obvious? Bergen wondered. It was something that Pre\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
scott did not want to say without elaborate preliminaries. The President appeared almost to be rambling. Why should he be talking about the procedures for sterilizing infected areas, and in the same breath as the tragedy at Denver? Those procedures had be
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n worked out and accepted by all parties. Could it be something new in the costs?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I agree, sir, that the economic realities are a prime consideration,\'94\loch\f0  Bergen said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He listened then while Prescott played out this gambit. The costs, although now \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 thousands of times greater than for any other disaster in human history, were clearly only a part of the President
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s immediate concern. Could he be thinking of sterilizing the Denver complex? Bergen wondered. The thought set his hand trembling with the te\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ephone against his ear. Bergen, a man who could talk bluntly when it was required of him, asked the question straight out.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The facilities, not the people,\'94\loch\f0  Prescott said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Bergen heaved a sigh of relief. There was too much death already. This mea\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
nt, however, that the rumored Colorado Plague Reservation was a reality. Infected men were to be isolated there. Why couldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t the DIC team be sent there, then?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Could The Team work effectively without the DIC facilities?\'94\loch\f0  Bergen asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Prescott d\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 id not think so.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     Bergen weighed this factor in his mind. Obviously, Prescott and his advisors needed the Denver military facilities. The DIC complex there could be sterilized and made useful once more for the military. But what of The Team?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 They\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  saved us days in identifying how the plague was spread,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Bergen said. \'93\loch\f0 And now that we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
ve confirmed it was O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill, surely the four men\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The President interrupted. He did not want to isolate such brilliant minds. But what was to be done with them wh\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
en the DIC was put to the fire? There was no comparable facility available in the Colorado Reservation.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      On a sudden hunch, Bergen asked: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Could they be sent to that new facility in England?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The President was full of immediate and fulsome praise \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 for this brilliant suggestion. Only a genius could have thought of it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Bergen took the red phone away from his ear and stared at it, then brought the instrument back to his ear. Praise was still pouring from it. He stared across the office at the pane\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
led wall, the dark wood door. His desk chair was the best the Danes could supply and he leaned back in it, the phone still at his ear. A child could have made the suggestion to send those men to England, but Bergen was beginning to see the President
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s pol\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 tical problem.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      If the four infected men of The Team from the DIC were on an airplane, they might crash in an uninfected region. The crash site would require the \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Panic Fire.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Bergen raised this question with Prescott, listening for subtle hints i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n the President\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s response.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Yes, it was too bad the press and public would not accept the official label, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Newfire.\'94\loch\f0 
 The words panic and fire had particularly noxious connotations when used together that way. More was beginning to emerge, however.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0    \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
  Even if a sealed aircraft did not crash, any new plague outbreak beneath the flight path could arouse powerful suspicions that the occupants had spread the infection, that it had somehow escaped and fallen upon more innocent victims. Demagogues were hav
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ng a field day and it would not do to provide them and the nut fringe of fanatics with more ammunition.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I think the French might be willing to supply an escort of fighter planes,\'94\loch\f0  Bergen said. He looked at the door to the outer officer while Prescott\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 showered him with more praise. The French ambassador was among a group patiently waiting to have lunch with him. A word or two in quiet, perhaps?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Mr. President, you are more than generous,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Bergen said, cutting off the new flow of praise. \'93\loch\f0 Can you g\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
et volunteers for their flight crew?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Again, the secretary-general listened. How fortunate that Doctor Beckett of The Team was a pilot \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 Air Force Reserve of all things! And Prescott had this knowledge at his fingertips. How well informed he was! And \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
a long-range aircraft could be made ready. The four men would drive themselves to the airport. They would take off, pick up their escort \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  and their car and its surroundings would receive its bath of Panic Fire.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Oh, there was one more thing. Could the\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  secretary-general arrange for the four men to receive positions of \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 useful importance\'94\loch\f0 
 at the facility in England?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Useful importance, Bergen mused.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      He decided on a small fishing expedition. \'93\loch\f0 Is it the wisest choice to send them to England? That \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
lab at Killaloe in Ireland sounds impressive, especially with all of the new equipment you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re providing.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But you yourself suggested England,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Prescott said. \'93\loch\f0 I naturally assumed, since it was your first suggestion, that the British facility was the 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 superior one.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 England it is,\'94\loch\f0  Bergen agreed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It was all very clear now. If anything went wrong, then it was the idea of the secretary-general of the United Nations. It was Bergen, after all, who made the essential arrangements and pushed this p
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 roject through.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The red phone at Bergen\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s ear had still more tidbits to reveal, however. Prescott had things to say about O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Neill. Bergen looked at his wristwatch while he listened. The hunger pangs were intense. Abruptly, he lifted his chin, startled\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 They think O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s in England?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  the secretary-general asked. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why do they think that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      As Prescott explained, it made a terrible logic. The victims, if they exposed him, might be afraid to retaliate lest the Madman loose an even more terribl\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e disaster upon them. O\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 Neill had threatened this in one of his letters, after all, and without more certain knowledge, no one could afford the assumption that he was bluffing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why not Ireland?\'94\loch\f0  Bergen asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Ah, yes. O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s features were kno\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 wn to some people in Ireland and even if he disguised himself\'85\loch\f0 
 well, the psychological people thought the Irish more prone to heedless revenge. Surely, O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill would have considered this. It was logical that he would want to hide in an English-speaking co\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 u
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ntry where he was little known and where he could blend into the background more easily. And there was England, a certain amount of chaos and disruption. And England was one of his target areas, a place where he had expressly forbidden those Outside to em
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 p\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 loy atomic sterilization.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     It made terrifying sense, but even more, if accurate, it exposed the workings of a mind that could cut through a problem like the slash of a sword. Bergen had a certain awareness of this quality in himself. Complexities must 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 be reduced to manageable shape and size, even if this involved pulling from a complexity only that which could be managed. Mad, O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill might be, but also a genius \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 a true genius.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 How much certainty do they attach to this idea?\'94\loch\f0  Bergen asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 h, yes: the Profile. This was more of the DIC Team\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s doing. Prescott and others believed The Team was \'93\loch\f0 getting into the Madman\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 \hich\f0 s mind, learning to think the way he does.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Bergen silently agreed. Perhaps they were doing this. Certainly, someone must do\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I will make the preliminary arrangements for the flight to England,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Bergen said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
Someone from my office will call on your people to work out the details.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Having achieved his object without ever openly expressing it, the President was wil\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ling to let the secretary-general go to lunch. There was even a suggestion that they get together soon for a round of golf and, then, finally, a more somber note.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Terrible times, yes,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Bergen agreed. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 These are, indeed, terrible times, sir.\'94
