\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That sounds rather cold-\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 blooded,\'94\loch\f0  Prescott said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t mean it that way. We have to address these emergencies by a priority system, which we both understand very well. Will you do your part in this, Adam?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Shared responsibility,\'94\loch\f0  Prescott said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s what I h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ad in mind, Adam.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll do my best, Hab.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      As the President returned his phone to the cradle in the lounge of the main lodge at Camp David, he looked at Charlie Turkwood, who stood at the fireplace, back to the flames.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That son-of-a-bitch B\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ergen just called in his counter,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Prescott said. \'93\loch\f0 And it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a doozy.\'94

