\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Fintan Craig Doheny was more than five minutes into the private conversation with Kevin O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell before realizing that his own life was on the line. D\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
oheny had always known Kevin was a killer, but had thought the need for the Doheny medical expertise was protection enough.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Apparently not.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They had come together into one of the new cell-offices in Kilmainham Jail at Kevin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s request. Doheny did \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
not like Kilmainham. Its choice as a central control point for Dublin Command had been a Finn Sadal move \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 for historic reasons.\'94\loch\f0 
 The place repelled Doheny. Every time he walked across the inner court with its wire-guarded walkway all around, the giant cur\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 v\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ed skylight overhead, he thought of the men who had lived \hich\f0 
\endash \loch\f0  or died \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0   in the minuscule cells that ringed the area: Robert Emmet, Patrick McCann, Charles Parnell\'85
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      But Kilmainham Castle and the Royal Hospital were less than a block away and Doheny was \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 forced to admit that the hospital facilities were excellent.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      The meeting had begun calmly enough when they entered the cell-office shortly after breakfast. Kevin had received a \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 general circulation\'94\loch\f0 
 report about the Killaloe Lab. When both of them wer\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e seated, a tiny desk and one light on it between them, Kevin said:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Themselves say our only hope is the Lab.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 If we ourselves are first to find the cure, the whole world must come to us,\'94\loch\f0  Doheny said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 The Lab, that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s not much hope after a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll this time,\'94\loch\f0  Kevin said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We have as much chance at it as anyone.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      It was as though Kevin had not heard. \'93\loch\f0 But we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re used to disappointments in Ireland. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve come to expect them.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 He leaned back and stared at Doheny. \'93\loch\f0 Anything else is the true \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 unexpected.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s defeatist talk, Kevin. I tell you Adrian Peard is as fine a mind as I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve ever met.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Kevin opened a drawer of his desk, brought out a small Belgian automatic pistol and placed it on the desk near his right hand.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I think \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 often of that young medical student and his woman in that tank,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kevin said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
Them holding each other in the night while the rest of us go lonely to our beds.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doheny looked at the pistol, feeling a chill in his stomach. What was happening here? And w\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
hat was this hypocritical talk about young Browder and Kate? It was common knowledge how the Beach Boys treated any surviving woman off the coffin ships. And the way Kevin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s people often killed outsiders driven ashore because of plague contamination. Hunt\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ng these \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 shore birds\'94\loch\f0 
 was considered sport by the Finn Sadal. Then burning the poor fellows in the old Celtic way \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  confined in wicker baskets over flames! This Kevin O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Donnell was a cruel man and that pistol on the desk could not be an idle gesture.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s on your mind, Kevin?\'94\loch\f0  Doheny asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I wonder who\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll be the last man in Ireland?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kevin asked. \'93\loch\f0 Some think it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ll be that wee wain in Athlone, the one taken alive from his dead mother. Where should I place my money, Fin?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I haven\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t the s\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 lightest idea. If I were you, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d not bet. There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s still a few women around.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s those think it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll be that boy being trained by the priests in Bantree,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kevin said. \'93\loch\f0 And then there
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s \hich\f0 \lquote \loch\f0 the Gypsy boy of Moern\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0  \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  himself already eight, but from a f\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
amily where many lived past one hundred. Do you fancy him, Fin?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve no concern except the plague,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
ve nothing before us but a desperate search for the cure. And Adrian Peard\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s people are\'85\'94
