\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      There goes the fire to be renewed, Doheny thought.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The Irish past was a sullen ember, always ready to erupt. Melancholy could become in an inst\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ant the berserker\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s abandon. It was hatred of the English; that was the hub of their lives. Each new Irishman pledged that a thousand years of cruelty would be avenged. It was ground into the Irish soul.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It is the source of our passion, the grim aspec\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 t behind every jest. And the object of our hatred was never more than sixty miles away across the Irish sea.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Oh, Kevin was easy to understand, but he would be harder to stop.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doheny pushed himself away from the cold wall of Kilmainham Jail. Sweat\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  was chilly against his skin. He turned and headed for the Royal Hospital.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      I must call Adrian immediately.
