\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doctor Dudley Wycombe-Finch knew what his people thought of this working office he had\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  chosen \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 much too small for the director of the all-important English Research Establishment, too cluttered and too remote from the centre of things here at Huddersfield.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      In the days when Huddersfield had been devoted to the physical sciences, this h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ad been the basement office of a research assistant. The building above it stood on the perimeter of the fence-enclosed grounds. It was a three-story concrete structure with no ivy and little character. Wycombe-Finch did maintain another office \'93
\loch\f0 for state\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 occasions\'94\loch\f0 
 back in the Administration Building. That was a spacious oaken suite with thick rugs and barriers of administrative assistants in the outer rooms, but this little cubicle and its adjoining lab was where he was to be found most of the time \hich\f0 
\endash \loch\f0  her\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 in an enclosure of windowless walls covered by bookshelves, its one door leading into the small laboratory. The desk was small enough that he could reach the farthest corner easily with either hand. The one chair was comfortable, high-backed and swiveled
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  And here he kept his radio and the listening devices and the electronic tools.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He leaned back in the chair and puffed on his long, thin-stemmed pipe while waiting for the morning call from Doheny. He and Doheny had met on several occasions at interna\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
tional conferences and Wycombe-Finch could picture his Irish counterpart when they spoke on the telephone \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 a short, rather stout man with a blustery manner. Wycombe-Finch was a contrasting tall, thin, gray-mantled figure. An American colleague once, seei\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
g him with Doheny, had called them Mutt and Jeff, labels that Wycombe-Finch had found offensive.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A dottle of bitter nicotine burbled out of his pipe stem, burning his tongue. Wycombe-Finch wiped away the offending particles with a white linen handkerc\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
hief, which he realized belatedly was one from the bottom of the drawer, one of those his wife, Helen, had laundered before\'85\loch\f0  He veered his mind away from that channel.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Outside the small office, he knew, the morning was a cold and misty grayness, all d\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 istances lost in the drifting diffusion. A Lakes Country morning, they called it locally.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The telephone in front of him weighted a scattering of papers \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  reports, summations. He stared at them while he smoked and waited. The telephone link between Ire\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
land and England was none too satisfactory at best and he had learned to be patient in dealing with these regular exchanges between himself and Doheny.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The telephone buzzed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      He put the instrument to his ear, laying aside the pipe in an ashtray. \'93\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Wycombe-Finch here.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doheny\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s distinct tenor was identifiable despite a poor connection that provided static and distinct clicks. Lots of listeners, Wycombe-Finch thought.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Ahhh, there you are, Wye. The damnable phone service is at its worst this\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  morning.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     Wycombe-Finch smiled. He had last met Doheny at a London conference on interdisciplinary cooperation. Jolly fellow and with a first-class scientific mind behind those wide blue eyes. It was only during these regular telephone exchanges, tho
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ugh, that they had formed what Wycombe-Finch thought of as a working friendship.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doe and Wye.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They had fallen into this first-name familiar relationship by the third call.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m convinced the telephone was created to teach us patience, Doe,\'94\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 Wycombe-Finch said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Stiff upper lip and all that, eh?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 Well, what\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s new, Wye?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve a new government boffin coming down this morning for an assessment of our progress,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Wycombe-Finch said. \'93\loch\f0 I know the chap 
\hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  Rupert Stonar. No hea\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 d for science but very alert to wool over the eyes.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Stonar,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve heard of him. Political.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Oh, very.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What do you have to tell him?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Bloody nothing. Plodding, that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s what we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re doing. Good plodding, the kind that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
produce in time but no big breakthrough, which is what Stonar and his people want.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 What about those four new people you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve added? The American, Beckett \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  I hear he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s the one figured out how the Madman spread this thing.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Brilliant fellow, no d\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 oubt of it. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve kept the four of them together as a team. There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s something about the way they work together. I hesitate to call it electric, but they are one of those happy associations that often produce great things.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Tell that to Stonar.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 He already knows it. I was hoping you might produce a little tidbit we could share with him, Doe.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      After a moment\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s silence, Doheny said: \'93\loch\f0 We don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t hide very much from you, do we, Wye?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Wycombe-Finch recognized this approach, part of a subtle cod\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
e he and Doheny had worked out between the lines. Doheny had something to reveal, something hot that his masters might resent his telling, but that wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t matter now because Wycombe-Finch obviously already knew it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I hope you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t even try,\'94\loch\f0  Wycom\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 be-Finch said, picking up on his side. \'93\loch\f0 
God knows I resent the use of spies, and I assure you, Doe, that we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re being completely candid with you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doheny\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s laughter rattled in the phone. Wycombe-Finch smiled gently. What in the devil had Doheny come up\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  with?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Well,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said, \'93\loch\f0 it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s true. We may have O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill himself.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Wycombe-Finch took advantage of a long burst of static to ask sharply: \'93\loch\f0 What? I didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t hear that.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The Madman. We may have him here.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You have the fellow in durance\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 , interrogators and all that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 God in heaven, no! I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 m sending him the long way to our facility at Killaloe. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s using the name John Garrech O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
Donnell. Claims to be a molecular biologist.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 How sure are you?\'94\loch\f0  Wycombe-Finch could feel his heart b\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
eating rapidly. No telling who might be listening to this conversation. Very dangerous. Doheny had to answer that question correctly.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re not positive, Wye. But I tell you, he tickles my neck hairs. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve one of our best men clinging to him like a \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
leech, a priest ready at hand should he wish to confess, and a poor bereaved young boy in the party so he can see constantly what he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s done.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Wycombe-Finch shook his head slowly from side to side. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Doe, you are a bloody awful man. You set this up.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0   \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0    \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I took advantage of a situation that was handed to us.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re still bloody clever, Doe. Conscience, that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll be the key to the fellow, that is if we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
re to believe that profile the Americans produced. My God! This does take a little thinking. I co\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 nfess I doubted it when our cloak-and-dagger boys told me.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re not getting our hopes up too high, but it is something to tell your man Stonar.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 He probably already knows. I suggest you be very careful, Doe. O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill may have some new nastines\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 s up his sleeve\'85\loch\f0 
 that is, if it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s the Madman.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Kid gloves, that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s the way we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re doing it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Terribly muddy waters, Doe.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      This referred to a joke they had exchanged at a conference, muddy waters being the most fertile for new growth.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Do\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 heny picked up on it immediately. \'93\loch\f0 Very roiled, indeed. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll let you know if they get muddier.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Quite. Are the Americans helping?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We haven\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t said anything to them for the obvious reasons, Wye. Earlier, they did send us some material\'85\loch\f0  just in c\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ase, but it
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s very scanty. No fingerprints, no dental records. They blame the Panic Fire, which may be the actual case.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And if this\'85\loch\f0  O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell, you say? If he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s just what he says he is?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re going to give him the mental thumbscrews: a triple\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  approach, all adding up to one thing \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 he must come up with a brilliant new approach to our researches.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Triple approach? Ahh, you mean in case he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s actually O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill and you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re unable to prove it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Damned right. He could give us a real clue, o\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 r try artful concealment or a diversion.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Or actual sabotage.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 As good as a confession, that.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  A burst of static, painfully loud, intruded on the line. When it passed, Doheny could be heard saying \'93\loch\f0 . . . Beckett\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s group is doing.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Wycombe-\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Finch took it as a question. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
I think the fellow to watch there is the little frog, Hupp. Got a devious mind. He feeds things to Beckett, almost as though he were playing Beckett, using the man as a personal computer.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Blimey! As you Brits say.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We say nothing of the kind, you Irish potato-eater.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Both chuckled. It was a weak enough chiggering, Wycombe-Finch thought, not enough to fool the listeners, but it had become almost ritual between them now, signaling that they were near the end of 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 the conversation.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 If we ever meet face to face again, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll whip your ears with my shillelagh \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  if I can find one of the blasted things,\'94\loch\f0 
 Doheny said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A tear slid down Wycombe-Finch\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s left cheek. The stereotypes had been laid out to be chuckled a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
t, but could they be discarded? Perhaps they played this game to keep the mistakes of the past fresh in their minds \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 brolly against shillelagh, the ridiculous against the ridiculous. A sigh shook Wycombe-Finch and he thought he heard its echo from Doheny\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll fill Stonar with visions of sugarplum faeries from Ireland,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Wycombe-Finch said, \'93\loch\f0 but your man O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
\hich\f0 Donnell is probably just what he says.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A molecular biologist is a molecular biologist,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d use Jesus, Mary and Joseph themse\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
\hich\f0 lves if they showed up.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Donnell carry any identification?\'94\loch\f0  Wycombe-Finch asked, speaking as the thought hit him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 A thick-head in command of the party that met him threw away the man\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s passport.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Threw it away?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Over his sh\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 oulder into the sea. No chance to scrutinize it now and determine if it was a forgery.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Doe, I think sometimes we are the victims of a deliberately malign fate.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Let\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s pray there is a balancing benevolent fate. Perhaps it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s Beckett\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s team.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0    \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0   \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 By the by, Doe, Beckett and his people think the zipper theory may be confusing us, leading us down the garden path, so to speak.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Interesting. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll pass it along.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Sorry I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve nothing more substantial for you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Wye, a thought just occu\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 rs to me. Why don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
t you put Stonar together with Beckett? Brilliant Yank explaining the intricacies of marvelous scientific research to uninformed politician.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Might be interesting,\'94\loch\f0  Wycombe-Finch agreed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It could even spark some new ideas in B\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 eckett,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Explaining things to the uninitiated sometimes does that.
\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll give it a think. Beckett, when he gets going, can be quite fluent.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d like to talk to Beckett myself. Could he join us for one of these confabs?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 l arrange it. Hupp, too?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  just Beckett. Perhaps Hupp later. And please prime Beckett for heavy interrogation, would you, Wye.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 As I say, he is quite fluent, Doe.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      There was silence filled with static for a moment, then Wycombe-Finch sa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 id: \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll put together a report on their ideas about the zipper theory. We
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll fax it to you first thing. Might be something in it, although I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m not giving ground.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Beckett needs resistance, eh?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It primes him well. Keep that in mind when you ta\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 lk.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Does he get angry?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Never shows it, but it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s there.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Fine! Fine! I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll be at my Yankee-baiting best. And as far as this possible Madman is concerned, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll let you know if the waters get muddier.
\'94
