There is one thing more, Doe. Stonar may be coming here to dismiss me.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Tell him to cut the phone lines to us if he does.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Now, Doe, don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t burn any bridges.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I mean it! We Irish don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t take naturally to you Brits. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll not waste my time breaking in another contact at Huddersfield. You tell him.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It only took us a week to get on a solid footing.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Nowadays, a week is forever. The politicians have\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t figured that out yet. They need us, we don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t need them.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Oh, I think we do, Doe.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We stand together, Wye, or the whole bloody edifice comes crashing down. You tell that Stonar I said so. Until next time, then?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 As you say, Doe.\'94
