an, bitter over the centuries of British oppression. He felt a tribal loyalty to his people and the land, a kinship of the rath. }{\i\dbch\af11\insrsid3359690 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 There was a pulling force in the Irish earth}{
\dbch\af11\insrsid3359690 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 , he thought. It was a memory that lived in the soil itself. It remembered and alwa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ys had. Even if there were no more people, there would be something here, an essence that would tell how the Gaels had passed this way once.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael was talking to the Yank, not probing, not doing what he should to see if it was a mask the man \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 wore and the Madman himself underneath. Black thoughts in his mind, Herity listened.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 There are more ruins now,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You noticed that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Destruction, it seems,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  John said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But plenty of food.\'94
