 it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s just tumbledown.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They fell silent, passing another burned cottage whose walls butted up against the road. The blank windows exposed ashed tatters of curtains like w\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ounded eyelids.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Someone will answer for that, Herity thought.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He felt the long Irish memory barbed like a spear. Offend it and someday you would feel the thrust and see your life welling from the wound.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They crested the top of the hill then \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
and paused for breath, looking ahead to the long curve of another valley stretched out into mists at the upper end where a stream cascaded off black rocks, making its mark on the air with a moist screen that hid the farther hills. A hen cackled nearby.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0    \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0   Herity cocked an ear, hearing the gurgle of water; a brook or a spring.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I hear water,\'94\loch\f0  John said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We could do with a bit of rest and some food,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He crossed to the lower side of the road where tall grass covered a lon\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
g slope into trees. Finding a spot in the stone wall where he could swing himself across, he went a few paces out into the tall grass. The boy leaped the wall and joined the priest.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked up at the sky. Clouds were coming in, filling the western\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 horizon. He glanced at Herity, who waved for him to join the priest and boy. John climbed onto the wall and stood there looking across the open land before jumping down. The landscape had been defined by gray rock walls into green rectangles with a few c
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ttages, all black and roofless, sprinkled among them. He heard Herity cross the wall and come up beside him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a beauty to it yet,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John glanced at him, then returned his attention to the view. The thin mist reduced the middle\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 distances to muted pastels, a rolling meadowland with a river winding through it, tall trees and darker greens on the far side.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Are you thirsty, Mister O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Donnell?\'94\loch\f0  Herity asked. But he looked at O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill as he spoke.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I could do with a cool drin\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 k of spring water,\'94\loch\f0  John agreed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m thinking you have no knowledge of thirst,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 A cool glass of Guinness with foam as white as a virgin\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 s panties flowing over the edges. Now there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s a vision to raise a man\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s thirst!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  and the boy began walking toward the trees below the meadow.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I heard you and the priest talking about the ruins,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s not ruins. Decay! That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s the word. Hope destroyed finally.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The priest and the boy stopped short of the trees n\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ear a granite outcropping. Looking after them, Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 A fine man, the priest. Wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
t you agree, Mister O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Donnell?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      At the jibing question, John felt O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill-Within begin to rise. Panic threatened him, then rage. \'93\loch\f0 Others have suffered as much \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 as you, Herity! You
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re not alone!\'94
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A flush of blood darkened Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s face. His lips tightened into a thin line and his right hand went toward the pistol under his jacket but hesitated and lifted instead to scratch the beard stubble on his chin.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Would you listen to us now?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he asked. \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re like a couple of wains in\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He broke off, stopped by the loud report of a shot from down in the trees below them. In one motion, Herity knocked John off his feet into the grass, rolled away with one hand\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 in his pack, and before he stopped rolling had a small machine gun in his hands and was scrambling down to the shelter of the granite outcropping. He stopped there, peering down into the trees. John was right behind him, leaning up against the cold stone
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John peered around his edge of the rock, looking for the priest and the boy. Were they hurt? Who had shot and where had it been aimed? A limb cracked below him and Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s pale and hatless head poked out of covering bushes under the trees. H\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
e was a wide-eyed blob of white against the green-and-brown background, the scar on his forehead very plain against the pale skin. He was staring directly up at John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Get your face back in here!\'94\loch\f0  Herity said. He yanked John back into the rock\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s cover\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I saw Father Michael. He seems to be all right.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And the boy?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t see him.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll be patient a bit,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That was a rifle shot.\'94\loch\f0 
 He cradled the machine gun against his chest and leaned back, scanning the rock wall \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 bordering the road above them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked at the weapon in Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s hands.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Seeing John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s attention, Herity said: \'93\loch\f0 The Jews make fine guns, now don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t they?\'94\loch\f0 
 He whirled at the sound of swishing grass below them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked up to see Father M\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ichael peering down at them. The black felt hat once more covered the brand-scarred forehead.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity scrambled to his feet and peered past the priest toward the trees. \'93\loch\f0 Where\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s the boy?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Safe behind some more boulders down there in the trees.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0     \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Only the one rifle shot,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Likely someone shooting a cow or a pig.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Or himself, that being the more common thing nowadays.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re a man full of evil,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. He pointed at the machine gun. \'93\loch\f0 Where did you ge\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
\hich\f0 t that terrible weapon?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 This fine Uzi made by the clever Jews, I took it off a dead man, Father Michael. Isn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t that where we get most things nowadays?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What do you intend with it?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 To use it if need be. Exactly wher\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 e did you leave the boy?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael turned and pointed at the gray gleam of more rocks just within the trees, the granite partly hidden by invading gorse.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We will go down there one at a time,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 I will go first, Mister O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 next, then you, Priest. Stay here until I call.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Crouching low, Herity darted from behind the rocks and ran zig-zagging down the slope into the trees. They saw him duck behind the other rocks, then his voice called:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Just the way I did it!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  John darted from behind the boulder, feeling exposed and vulnerable as he ran down the slope \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 left, right, left and into a pocket between the rocks where he saw the boy crouched, huddled into the blue coat. There was no sign of Herity. The boy stared at\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 John with a blank expression.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      There came the sound of running and Father Michael joined them, putting a protective arm around the boy.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity reappeared then, trotting up from deeper in the trees. He joined them in the rock shelter, breathing hea\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 vily, the machine gun held at the ready across his chest.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 The three of you will stay here until I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve looked over the land below us,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
That was a foolish thing you did, Priest, sauntering up there through the open after such a shot.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 If God means me to go now, He will take me now,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Or so you hoped,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s a sin, Father. Remember that. When you court death, how is that different from deliberate suicide?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael cringed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 started to leave but John detained him with a hand on his arm. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Joseph.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity turned a surprised look at John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m grateful for your concern,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  John said. \'93\loch\f0 And I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d like you to call me John, but I\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll not change one word of what I said up there.\'94\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He gestured with his chin up the hill toward where Herity had knocked him down to protect him. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I meant every word of it.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity grinned. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Of course you did, Yank!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      With that, Herity ducked from behind the sheltering rocks and ran down into the\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  trees. They heard a limb crack, then silence.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A strange man, that,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The boy pulled away from the priest and peered over the sheltering rocks.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Here! Stay down!\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said. He pulled the boy back.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Herity\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  acts like a soldier,\'94\loch\f0  John said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That he does.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Where did you encounter him?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael looked away, hiding his face from John, but not before John saw a look of near panic there. What was it between those two \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  the priest and the vi\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
olent man of action?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Father Michael spoke in a choked voice: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You might say God threw Joseph and me together. The reason for it, I cannot say.\'94\loch\f0  He returned his gaze to John, the features composed.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What about the boy?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  John asked. \'93\loch\f0 Why is he with\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  you?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A band of tinkers gave him to me,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d call them Gypsies, but they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re not really, y
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  know. They treated him well. They were the ones told me of his vow of silence.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Then he can talk?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve heard him cry out \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 in his sleep.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The boy closed his eyes and bowed his head into the blue jacket.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Has he a name?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Only he can say and he won\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Have you made any attempt to find his\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Hush now!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael glared at John. \'93\loch\f0 Some \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 pains are best not poked at, man.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John turned his head away abruptly, trying to control a rictus grin. There was a pain in his breast. He could feel O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Neill-Within moving closer and closer to the surface. John put both hands over his face, trying to \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 quell the dangerous Other. A sound of tumbling pebbles brought his face jerking up out of his hands.
