\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 o the barn before he saw me.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You told Father Michael he was dead.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That I did. And him coming at me with a billhook! What could I do?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity grinned at him and patted the machine gun. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
He had a whole bag of ammo for it, as well.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      At supp\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 er, John watched Murphey and Gannon, observing the accuracy of Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s assessment.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      How does Herity judge me? John wondered.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It was an unsettling thought. He looked at Herity seated across from him, busily spooning the marrow into his mouth.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  He trusted me with the machine gun.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It had been a test, John decided. From Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s reactions, John guessed the test had been passed. But it did not do to let your guard down with this man.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They ate at the long table in the kitchen \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  a checkered\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 red cloth on it, heavy dishes, water in tall glasses with ridged sides. The pork had been boiled with some wild leafy green that gave it a tart, rather pleasant flavor and cut the greasiness. Gannon had the kitchen manner of someone who had cooked for pl
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 asure and not lost the touch.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d make somebody a lovely wife,\'94\loch\f0  Herity joked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Gannon did not rise to the barb. Murphey had glowered at Gannon, pinched face drawn into a tight scowl, which changed to a smile when Herity looked at him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Hav\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 e you noticed, John,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity asked, gesturing with his table knife, \'93\loch\f0 
how the passions are burnt out of the Irish? I do believe the Madman himself could walk into our midst without harm, and him covered with the blood of all those millions. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d only make \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 r
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 oom for him at table and ask did he want a drink?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s not apathy,\'94\loch\f0  Gannon said. It was his first remark since bringing the food to the table.
