\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael had sent the silent boy to bed and had taken a position at t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
he end of the long table as far as he could get from the drinkers, but his eyes were on the glasses of poteen, not on the men. Gannon had sent the other children off to their beds and had busied himself cleaning up at the sink.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John, bringing his cup \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 from the parlor, had handed it to Gannon and seated himself near the priest. Looking at the branded forehead, he thought about the question of the priest\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 s family.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Where are your brothers, Father Michael?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael turned a hunted look tow\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ard John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You said you have two brothers.\'94
