 Wycombe-Finch glanced at the staff members, who were slowly filing out of the room, none of them meeting the director\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s gaze. \'93\loch\f0 But he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll have his spies here and one of them\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s sure to explain it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Then he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll know about the carrot as well as\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  the stick.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Politicians don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t like sticks in other people\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s hands. Carrots either, for that matter.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re quite excited by the implications,\'94\loch\f0  Beckett said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Wycombe-Finch glanced at Hupp, still seated in the big chair. The room was almost\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  empty.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I do believe,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  the director said, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 that Doctor Hupp is not as excited as you are, Bill. Doctor Hupp appears to be asleep.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Well, what the hell!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Beckett said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We did work all night.\'94
