ve been out of government for a long time, Shiloh. I know you have important contacts, but they may not be telling you everything they know.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And you are?\'94\loch\f0  There was anger in the old diplomat\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I have adopted a policy of increasi\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ng candor \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  not complete, but trending that way.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Shiloh Broderick absorbed this in silence.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The plague had produced a new kind of consciousness in most powerful people, Velcourt had noted. It was not just adapting to a sequence of new political \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
situations but a different level of awareness, more penetrating. It put survival first and political games second. Politics had been reduced to its most personal level: Who do I trust? Whenever that question was asked at a life-and-death level, there coul
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 d\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  be only one answer: I trust the people I know.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      I know you, Shiloh Broderick, and I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t trust you.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Mister President,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Broderick said, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 why did you invite me in here?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve had some experience of trying to get through the political barric\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ades, Shiloh, trying to reach the ear of someone who could \hich\f0 \lquote 
\loch\f0 do something.\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0   I have some sense of your present situation.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Broderick again leaned forward. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sir, out there\'85\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he pointed at the windows \'93\loch\f0 . . . are people who know things you need to know. I
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  represent some of the finest \hich\f0 \endash \'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Shiloh, you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve put your finger precisely on my problem. How do I find them? And having found them, how do I wade through and weed through what they bring?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You trust your friends!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Velcourt sighed. \'93\loch\f0 But, Sh\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 iloh, things presented to me\'85\loch\f0  well, things excluded are often more important than things presented. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
m the President, now, Shiloh. My first resolution is to weed out the advisors who produce only drama. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll listen once in case they bring something new, \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 b\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ut I don\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t have time for old nonsense.\'94
