\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Velcourt spoke first: \'93\loch\f0 Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t assume that I hold grudges. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve no time for such nonsense. What I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
m telling you is that I intend to rely on my own judgment. That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s the nature of this office. And the\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  record shows that my judgment has been better than yours. You have one value to me, Shiloh \hich\f0 
\endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  information.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      And Velcourt thought: Does Shiloh suspect the real nature of the information he brought me today? Broderick represented people who might act in\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
dependently to endanger an extremely delicate balance. An upset in these times could lead to a planet empty of humans. Broderick\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s people clearly were acting out of a context whose time had passed. Operation Backfire would have to be alerted.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Broderic\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 k\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s lips moved against each other but did not part, then, he spoke in a tightly controlled voice: \'93\loch\f0 We always said you weren\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 \hich\f0 t a very good team player.\'94
