mo was a first step. The aware people would have to be found\'85\loch\f0  the bright ones who were not afraid to report unpopular things.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Analysis in depth was a thing that had to happen outside the President\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s presence. Perhaps that had been the need for a long \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 time. It had taken the plague\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 s immediacy to supress all the drama-pushers and make this approach so obvious.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Broderick had been right on one thing, though: Find the right people. But when he found them, when he had digested their information and acte\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
d upon it, he had to make sure his orders were carried out. It was clear that the power of the people Broderick represented often transcended that of the transients who occupied the Oval Office. It even transcended the power of people in other offices, in
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 the corner offices or in the large spaces at the ends of long halls lined with portraits of past transients. Bureaucrats came to recognize early a simple truth about their powers: \'93
\loch\f0 We will be here after the transients have been replaced by the electorate.\loch\af0\dbch\af11\hich\f0 \'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Time was on their side.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Velcourt paused at the door to the East Room. Well, the plague had changed that, too. Time had only one use now \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  find the path to survival.
