\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The road beneath John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s feet crested the ridge at the top of\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 the valley much farther to the right of the slate-roofed mansion than he had expected. He could see a shallow swale on his right close with young pines, which thickened into taller pines at a higher crest beyond. At his left, a steep slope descended some
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
fifty meters before gentling into a deep bowl perhaps a thousand meters across. The chateau, three stories high and with four levels to its roofline, nestled into a black rock elbow at the far side of the bowl. Sheep cropped the meadow grass in front of t
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e building. A double line of poplars led in at an angle from far to the right, an overgrown lane between them. The poplars and a tall stand of evergreens partly concealed a deeper lawn beyond.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A wind from the west swayed the poplars and bent the tall \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
grass growing up through the rock fence along the road beside John. He turned to look at his companions. Herity had put one foot on the rock fence and leaned forward on the upraised knee, listening. Father Michael and the boy stood near him, staring at th
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  pastoral scene below them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Would you look at that now,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said, his voice hushed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael cupped a hand behind his left ear.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Listen!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John heard it then: the sounds of children playing \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  thin cries, excitement in the shou\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ts. }{\i\dbch\af11\insrsid3359690 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 A game}{
\dbch\af11\insrsid3359690 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 , he thought. He clambered onto the rock wall near Herity and stared off across the bowl toward the building. The sound came from beyond the poplars and the screening evergreens.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity removed his foot from the wall and trotted down the roa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 d until he was past the screening trees. John and the others hurried to follow.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael pulled Cannon\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s gift binoculars out of his pack as he ran. He stopped and aimed them at the flat expanse of lawn revealed from this new position. The others
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  stopped beside him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John saw them now \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  children played on the lawn, kicking a ball. They wore white blouses and matching stockings, black shoes and\'85\loch\f0  skirts! Dark skirts!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity reached a hand toward Father Michael. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Give me those binoculars!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0     Father Michael passed them to Herity, who focused them on the players. His lips worked soundlessly as he looked, then: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
Ahhh, the little beauties. The little beauties.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Slowly, Herity lowered the binoculars, then thrust them at John. \'93\loch\f0 See what the Mad\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 m\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 an missed?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     With trembling hands, John focused the binoculars and aimed them at the lawn. The players were girls of about twelve to sixteen years of age. Their hair had been done into twin braids, which swung wide as they ran and twisted after the bal
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 l shouting, calling out to other players. Some of the girls, John noted, wore yellow armbands, some green. Two teams.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 A girls\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  school?\'94\loch\f0  John asked, his voice husky. He could sense the faint and distant stirring of O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Neill-Within, querulous movement t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 hat he knew had to be stilled.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s Brann McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s little dovecote,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 
Him as made this little place off limits to the Finn Sadal and others and, it being common knowledge that McCrae has at least five rocket launchers plus other assort\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ed instruments of violence, the Military Council does not question his decree.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The silent boy crowded close to Father Michael, his gaze intent on the lawn.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John lowered the binoculars and returned them to the priest, who proffered them to the bo\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 y, but the boy only shook his head.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Is it really girls or is it boys dressed up as girls?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Girls and young women they are,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 all preserved in Mister McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s transplanted French chateau. Would you say that
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s a French ch\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ateau, John?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It could be.\'94\loch\f0  John was only conscious of his reply after he had spoken. He looked toward the building\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s roof, visible over the treetops. Smoke trailed from four of the building\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s chimneys. He could smell turf fires.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Joseph, why ha\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve we come this way?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael asked, his voice trembling. \'93\loch\f0 We must not go near that place. It\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 s certain sure we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re contaminated with the plague.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 As are the soldiers guarding them,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 But it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s isolation they have and we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll see them
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  through this patch alive. All the women of Ireland are not dead.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Who is this Brann McCrae?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The Croesus of imported farm machinery,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 A rich man, himself as has big houses such as this and guns and, so I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
m told, tough\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  women to use them.\'94\loch\f0 
 He turned away and, as he moved, a rifle shot sounded from the direction of the mansion. A bullet slammed into the rock wall beside him and went keening off in ricochet. Father Michael tumbled the boy to the road behind the wall. John
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ducked and found his arm gripped, Herity dragging him across the road. They rolled across the opposite wall as another bullet hit behind them. Father Michael and the boy squirmed across the road, crossed the wall and joined Herity and John. They lay in he
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 vy grass above the shallow, pine-filled swale John had noted earlier.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John listened. The sounds of girls at play were gone. A masculine voice barked a one-word command in the distance, the ringing sound of a bullhorn amplifier in it:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Inside!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0   \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0    \'93\loch\f0 They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re only warning us off,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Not Brann McCrae,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. He peered into the swale and the ridge beyond it. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Follow me.\'94\loch\f0 
 Keeping his head low, Herity ran down the shallow hill into the pines, crashing through branches, tu\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 rning to present his shoulder to the worst of the obstructions.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John and the others followed. John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s arms and shoulders were slapped and buffeted by springing limbs.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 In here!\'94\loch\f0  Herity called.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They burst through a screen of limbs to a small c\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
learing with cottage-size outcroppings of granite in its center. Herity dove behind the rocks, the others with him. They lay panting on grass that smelled of dust and flint. Father Michael crossed himself. The boy cowered against the priest.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Why are \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 we running?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Because I know Mister McCrae,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Silence settled over the clearing, then a hissing roar sounded from the mansion\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s valley. A deafening explosion erupted at the road they had just quit. Black shards of road sur
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 face and rock showered the area.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity looked at Father Michael. \'93\loch\f0 He doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t cooperate, that Brann McCrae.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s ears were ringing from the explosion. He put his hands over them and shook his head. O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within had stirred to something near \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
wakefulness. Explosions were only bombs to him, not rockets. Bombs killed your loved ones.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You have no loved ones left,\'94\loch\f0  John muttered.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What was that?\'94\loch\f0  Herity asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      John lowered his hands. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Nothing.\'94\loch\f0  He could feel O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within returning\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 to quiescence but there was no solace in this respite. What if O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within should come out fully in Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s presence? That would be disaster.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We must get away from here,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity raised a hand for silence. He stared off \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 into the pines to the north. A limb cracked there and something large could be heard moving through the branches. Herity pointed at John\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s pocket and mouthed the word: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Pistol.\'94\loch\f0  Placing a finger to his lips, his machine gun cradled close to his chest, Her\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ty crept off toward the sound, wriggling along under the branches. He was lost from view within only a few heartbeats.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John slipped the pistol from his pocket and stared after Herity. He felt foolish. What good was this little peashooter against a roc\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ket launcher? There was no more sound of the large something moving through the pines.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael had found a rosary and fingered the beads, his lips moving. The boy had pulled his head almost completely into his anorak.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The silence dragged o\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ut \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 oppressive, weighted. John crept forward past the priest and turned until he could sit up with his back against the warm rock of the outcropping. The low pines were directly in front of him only a few paces away, tall brown grass in the foreground, t
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ick green limbs beyond. It was an almost perfect screen to conceal anything outside the clearing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A masculine voice shouted from up toward the ridge on his right. John could detect no word in the sound. He felt exposed here, set out as a target for an\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
yone in the concealment of the trees. John lifted the revolver and cocked it. Sounds of movement in the pines \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  Herity?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yank!\'94\loch\f0  It was Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s voice. \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s friends. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re coming in.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John lowered the pistol, uncocked it and returned it to his po\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 cket.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity emerged from the trees followed by two tall men \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 scarecrows in green uniforms, dark green berets, the harp insignia of Eire at the shoulders and on the berets. Both carried automatic rifles. Herity held his machine gun casually cradled i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n his right arm.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     John studied the two men with Herity. They were enough alike to be twins, although the one in the lead appeared older, more lines around the eyes, skin somewhat more weathered. Wisps of sandy hair poked from beneath their berets. Thei
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 r pale blue eyes stared out warily over flat cheeks and short noses. They had softly rounded chins and full lips.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The three men strode up to the rock shelter as John and Father Michael arose. The boy remained seated, peering up from the hood of his an\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 orak.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The men stopped in front of John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 This is John Garrech O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell, Liam. Father Michael you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll be knowing. And this down here\'85\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 he glanced at the boy on the ground \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 . . . is the boy.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The older of the two newcomers nodded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      For John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s benefit, Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 This is Liam,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  indicating the older man, \'93\loch\f0 and his cousin, Jock. They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
re Cullens, the both of them. Liam and Jock are with the eight full squads of regulars to keep watch on Mister McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s fine establishment there, i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 t being a tempting morsel for unsavory types.
\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 God be praised,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Nothing must harm those young women.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Liam glanced at Father Michael, a heavy-lidded stare full of animosity. Seeing it, John wondered at this show of anger. T\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
here were undercurrents here that troubled John. Herity knew these two men. They knew Father Michael. The priest\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s early question was appropriate. Why had they come this way?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The Arrrmy be praised,\'94\loch\f0  Jock said, a heavy burr in his voice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He doesn\loch\af0\dbch\af11\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t sound Irish, John thought.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      As though he read John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s mind, Herity said: \'93\loch\f0 Doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t he have a wonderful sound in him, our Jock? He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s one of the Catholic Scots from Antrim, John.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Leave be,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Liam said. \'93\loch\f0 You knew that road was off-limits, Joseph. W\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 hy do you tempt McCrae and his rocket launcher?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 To use up his ammunition,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said, a chuckle in his voice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Aren\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t you the funny man!\'94\loch\f0  Liam said.
