\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It was dusk outside the White House, that strange Washington dusk which lingered and lingered, blending finally into the brilliant lights of the Capitol\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s night.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      P\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 resident Velcourt, looking out at the dusk and the lights coming on, thought he had never before been this tired. He wondered if he had the energy to get up from his chair and go to the cot he
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d had moved here into the Oval Office. But he knew if he once \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 p\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ut his head on the pillow, necessities would flood his mind. Sleep would not come \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 only the fatigue and the heart-draining need for action.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      What a day this had been!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It had started with Turkwood storming into the office, his expression black, to\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  slide the morning report onto the President\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s desk. Sometimes, Velcourt wondered at the advisability of inheriting Turkwood from Prescott. There were occasions when you needed someone who would do the dirty work, but Turkwood seemed tainted, perhaps untr\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 u
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 stworthy.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      As Turkwood had started to leave, Velcourt had asked: \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s wrong with you?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I just had to fire someone in communications.\'94\loch\f0  Again, Turkwood moved to leave.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Wait a minute. Why did you fire someone?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s not your problem, \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 sir.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Everything here\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s my problem. Why\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d you fire this person?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 He was using the White House channels to talk to friends in the Mendocino Reserve.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 How the devil could he do that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 He got at the satellite code somehow and was just\'85\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  well, rerouting to his friends.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I thought that was impossible.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Apparently not. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re questioning him right now to find out how he did it. He says he just worked it out.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s his name, Charlie?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Velcourt felt his pulse quickenin\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 g. A resourceful and independent mind right here in the White House.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 His name? It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s ahhh, David Archer.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Get him in here, Charlie! I want him here sooner than instanter.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Turkwood knew that tone. He ran out of the office.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      David Archer\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  was a pale young man with acne-scarred features and a hunted expression. His movement into Velcourt\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s office could only be described as slinking. Turkwood, wearing a grim expression, was right behind him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Velcourt put on his most affable expression, \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 his warmest tone of voice. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sit down, David. Is that what they call you? David?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  they call me DA, sir.\'94\loch\f0  He sat facing Velcourt.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 DA, is it?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Velcourt looked up at Turkwood. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You can leave us alone, Charlie. DA looks harmless to me.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      T\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 urkwood left, but there was reluctance in every movement. He spoke from the doorway before closing the door. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
You have that nine-fifteen appointment, sir. The phone conference.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll be right here, Charlie.\'94
