\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It no longer bothered John that he was forced to leave the vicinity of\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s chateau without spreading the plague there. He knew now that he was being saved for more important things at the Killaloe Lab. Nemesis remained true. Jock had saved him from a terrible error. Herity was confused. Had John merely been stumbling a
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 b\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 out blindly in the dark outside the telephone hut?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      By his intervention, Jock had also revealed Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s purpose. Herity was looking for O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      This amused John. With Herity nearby, O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within would never reveal himself. John Roe O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill lay\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 subdued, blocked by a fear-anesthesia. The nightmare screams were temporarily walled off. John O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell could stride along with his three companions, swinging his arms freely. He felt liberated.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Jock Cullen and four armed soldiers escorted them two \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
miles down the hill away from the chateau before returning their weapons. Herity checked his machine gun carefully, then looped its supporting strap around his neck. John merely slipped the pistol and ammunition into a hip pocket and pulled the yellow swe
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ter over it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      They parted at a crossroads where a signpost still pointed the way to Dublin. Jock gestured to the sign with the rifle: \'93\loch\f0 You know the way. Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t come back.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The consequences of disobedience did not have to be spoken. The escort turne\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
d and marched back up the hill, leaving John and his companions in the stone-bordered roadway. There were tall pines all around, but meadows could be glimpsed ahead where the road led down off the ridges.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John glanced at Herity. The man was like that \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
Japanese toy, the little dumpling doll with weights glued into its rolling bottom: six times down, seven times up. He would always return to the upright position. John felt amused by the idea of Herity returning to a standing position though dead. Somethi
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 g bitterly tenacious in him. Dangerous, He might be confused, but he would not stop hunting.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Let\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s be going!\'94\loch\f0  Herity said. He waved them ahead and aimed a kick at the boy, which the boy dodged.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      In that instant, John recognized the source of Heri\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ty\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s irritation with the boy. Here was a young lad\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s flesh, the shape and form that Herity could identify, but without animation except for that slumbering rage. The flesh was clumsy, like a mechanical toy left to run down and with its spring now almost u\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 wound.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Do something definite!\'94\loch\f0  Herity was saying.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      That was why Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s anger had been subdued by the boy\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s attack at the wash house. Something definite.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Within a mile, they came to a Y-branch in the road, no signpost here. Herity took the \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 right-hand way, but Father Michael stopped, the boy with him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Now just a minute, Joseph. That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s the long way by a good many miles.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t even pause. \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve been ordered to deviate via Dublin.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael hurried to catch up, bu\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 t the boy lagged behind with John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael demanded. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Who said?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Jock said. Orders from Dublin.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Father Michael glanced back at John, then at Herity. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Be still, you crazy priest!\'94\loch\f0  There was frustration in Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
voice. He quickened his pace, forcing Father Michael almost to trot. Their footsteps sounded muffled on the paving, enclosed by the border of thick trees and rock walls. John sensed a new tension in Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s manner \hich\f0 
\endash \loch\f0  quick glances left and right, the mach\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ne gun held ready in his hands.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael hitched his pack higher and fell back slightly. Herity eased his long strides, peering up and around.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked up through the trees: a peculiar light in the morning sky, as though everything came \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
through a gray filter. Distances were muzzy in diffusion, everything caught up in a sea-driven mist from the east. The sky directly overhead spread out a dark silver shaded into lighter steel eastward.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Breakfast lay heavy in John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s stomach \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  fresh bee\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 f and boiled nettles with potatoes. The chateau\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s guardians had set aside for their mess a small stone cottage of what had obviously been a substantial farmstead on a ledge cut off from McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s establishment by a long, slanting ridge. The cottage\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s inter\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 or walls had been crudely knocked out, opening space for a long table and rude benches. The food, cooked on a turf fire, had been served just after dawn, only John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s group and the escort at table.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity had arrived last with Jock beside him, the youn\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ger Cullen uneasy and trying to avoid conversation. But Herity had been full of questions.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John had eaten quietly, listening. There were things to be learned here. Liam had been called away by his command duties. The other guardians already were poste\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
d for their day duty around the chateau.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The other soldiers at the table, sensing something different in Jock\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s manner, kept a quiet watch. Slowly, tensions began to mount in the stone-walled cottage.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Father Michael broke the silence: \'93\loch\f0 God is put\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ting us through a sore test.\'94\loch\f0  The words sounded forced, leaving an even more intense silence behind them.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sure, Father, and which plague did you have in mind?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity asked. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Was it the plague of the papacy now?\'94\loch\f0 
 He spoke with unswerving arrogance.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0     \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s the use of blame?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Him asking such a question!\'94\loch\f0  Herity laughed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve much to answer for,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 
The British planted a bad seed amongst us, but I ask you now, where was that seed nurtured? Was i\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 t not ourselves seeing the fruit and plucking it from the branches?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Eve\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s apple it is!\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Only we called it the Proves of the IRA,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Jock said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A beautiful red apple with a bomb in it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s jaw clamped tight. A flush sprea\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 d over his face. He put both hands on the table. Violence wavered in the air.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Have done!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Are we not all paying the piper now?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Let us pay him then and have our little dance,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Jock said. \'93\loch\f0 Will y\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0  dance wi\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  me, Joseph?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0    \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0   \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Enough!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael thundered. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll curse the first one of you taking to violence!\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Jock swallowed convulsively, then in a low voice: \'93\loch\f0 Mayhap you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re right, Father. Best it were over and the world going on without such mischief.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity gl\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 owered at the priest. \'93\loch\f0 I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t fear your curses, Michael Flannery. But I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ll honor the truth in young Jock. He sees the way of things.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Father Michael sighed. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Joseph, you were a God-fearing man once. Will you never come back to the Church?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herit\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 y stared into his cold stew, oddly subdued by the sudden quenching of Jock\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s fire. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve lost me faith and that
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s what huddles me, true enough.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Then, why\'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Shut your fool mouth, priest! I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve no more respect for clerics, not after Maynooth. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 sooner melt their bells for drinking mugs than spend another minute in one of your churches!\'94\loch\f0  He pointed a death\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s-head grin at Father Michael. \'93\loch\f0 And if y\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
 call that blasphemy, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll tip y\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  into the first well we find.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Jock had led them down through t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
he fields away from the chateau, dew drenching their pants. They could see the paved road ahead, a farm lane entering it. There was one last glimpse of the chateau as the party rounded the barrier ridge. It was a gray castle wall nestled in the trees. Fai
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 tly, they heard the sound of children shouting.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Jock looked over his shoulder at the distant sound, pausing by a stile while the others climbed over onto the farm lane. As John passed, Jock looked at him. \'93\loch\f0 
It was mostly the girls learned the Irish dan\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ces,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They do their dances of a morning up there.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He pointed toward the chateau with his chin. \'93
\loch\f0 If we lose those girls, we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve lost it all \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  all of those beautiful dances. I think I can forgive McCrae anything if we don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t lose that.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      After J\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ock left them, John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s thoughts kept returning to those words \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  the half-hopeful sadness in them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity continued to march along at the point, an advance scout with his machine gun at the ready. Father Michael trailed behind him. John and the boy kept\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  pace at the rear.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     The road made a sharp left turn up ahead out of the flanking trees. Straight ahead beyond the turn, grass tufted around a jutting mound of pale granite. Herity stopped, motioning the others to stop behind him. John looked past Herit
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 y, wondering what had spooked him. All he could see was two sheep on a grassy shelf below the rocks. The sheep stared up at them full of alarm.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s only some sheep,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity waved a hand for silence. He studied their surroun\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 dings, the mounded hillocks below the outcropping, the empty valley beyond \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 a narrow place with a boggy stream down its middle.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s a wonder it is that you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re not dead long ago, Michael Flannery,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 
Whatever it is bothers those sheep sh\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ould bother us.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And what might be bothering them?\'94\loch\f0  the priest asked,
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I wonder where Liam went this morning?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity asked. \'93\loch\f0 Let us be goin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  back a ways, and silent as the tomb about it.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity backed up the road, keeping his attention on\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
