\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The third week out from McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s, Herity stopped them at nightfall beside a small, one-room cottage hidden from the road by a hillock. They reached it \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
on an overgrown track through the inevitable granite walls. John found himself pleasurably anticipating walls and a roof overhead. They had spent the previous night fireless, crouched in an abandoned hay shed while wind drove the rain around them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Ins\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ide, the cottage smelled of mildew, but the windows remained unbroken and the door sealed tightly. Herity came back from scouting the area to report there was no fresh food, not even chickens wandering in the yard to lead them to a nest of eggs.
