\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The rain seems to be slackening a bit,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a mild winter. Should we wait for him before we eat?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 If you wish.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Silence settled over the room with only the faint hissing of the pe\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
at fire in the background, the rain on the roof reduced to a light pattering. John became conscious of a second leak dripping near the first one. The boy snuffled loudly.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Abruptly, the door burst open and Herity entered swiftly, closing the door behin\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
d him. He wore a light poncho, which dripped a wide wet stain on the floor. There was a wild look in his eyes. He shook wetness off his green cap.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re not followed,\'94\loch\f0  he said. He slipped the poncho over his head, dropping the cap to the floor with \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
a damp plop. Under the poncho, the machine gun hung by its neck sling but their attention was caught by a string bag slung from Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s left shoulder. It contained three white plastic bottles and a jumble of canned food, the preplague commercial variety \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 w\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ith bright labels.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Now where did you find that lot?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity grinned. \'93\loch\f0 Provender for those on the run. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve buried caches of it all over Ireland.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve been this way before, then,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That I \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 have.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 He hung his poncho on a peg beside the door and plopped the string bag onto the table, sending it teetering precariously on its propped leg. \'93\loch\f0 Gannon\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s cheese,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 he said, looking at the table. \'93\loch\f0 A good supper that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll make but the meat\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s high. Would yo\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 u\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  be making us all sick, Priest?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t like to throw away food.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Ahhh, we still remember the starvation times, don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t we?\'94\loch\f0 
 Herity said. He picked up the packet of meat in its plastic wrapping and dropped it onto the fire. The grease flared bri\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
efly, sending an acrid smell of rancid pork and burned plastic through the room. Herity peered across the room at John standing near a window. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You know what pork smells like burning, John? Same as we would.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John remained silent.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity took up \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 a slab of hearth bread and covered it with cheese.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The priest and the boy came up to the table and followed Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s example. Father Michael passed a slab of bread and cheese to John, saying: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
Bless this food, Lord, for the keeping of our flesh.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 John ate beside the window staring outside. The storm had moved across the hills taking the rain with it. The eaves still dripped glistening pellets of water visible briefly as they passed the firelight shining out the window. The cheese had a faint toba
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 c\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 co smell and it tasted sour. John felt rather than heard Herity come up beside him. Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s breath smelled of the sour cheese and something else. John sniffed. Whiskey! John looked squarely at the man in the orange firelight. Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s eyes were steady, n\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 faltering in his movements.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve noticed, John, that you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t reminisce,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said, his voice even.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Nor do you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve noticed that, have you?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Is it something you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re hiding?\'94\loch\f0  John asked. He felt bold in this question, safe be\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 cause O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Neill-Within would never show himself in this man\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s presence.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A lopsided smile twisted Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s mouth. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The very question in me mind!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael turned his back to the fire and stared across the room, his eyes in shadows. The boy ret\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 urned to his position seated on the hearth.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve been wondering,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 how you come by your knowledge of Ireland?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A grandfather.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Born here?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 His father.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Where?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Cork.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John stopped himself on the point o\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 f repeating Grampa Jack\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s story of the seven hundred rifles. That might already have surfaced as part of the O\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 Neill background. A stillness came over his entire body as he thought about this. He knew there was a certain crazy prudence in his behavior. Th\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 reasoning evaded him, though. There was a connection between O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell and O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      I know the things O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill knew.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They were related, he decided. It was a troublesome relationship whose connections were to be avoided.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 So your ancestors we\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 re half Irish,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Full Irish.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Both sides. Isn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t that a marvel!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why all these questions, Joseph?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Call it me natural curiosity, John. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve been wondering, I have, where it was you did all your fiddling with microscopes a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
nd test tubes and the wonderful instruments of science?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked at the firelight glowing around Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s dark figure, the boy a motionless mound by his feet. They were like posed silhouettes.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Well now, he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s not answering,\'94\loch\f0  Herity sa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 id.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It was the University of Washington,\'94\loch\f0  John said. That was safe enough. The region had been hit by the Panic Fire even before he had left France.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 And I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll wager you were an important man,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Very minor.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 How is it you \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 escaped the troubles there?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Vacation.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity favored him with a long, measuring stare. \'93\loch\f0 Then you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re one of the lucky ones.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Like you,\'94\loch\f0  John said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Have you personal reasons for coming here to help?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 My reasons are none of your\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  business!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity turned to stare out the window beside them. His voice carried a reflexive undertone when he spoke. \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re right, Mister John O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
Donnell.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He aimed a twisted grin at the priest, a satanic look in the underlight from the fire. \'93\loch\f0 Isn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
that the Eleventh Commandment, Father? Thou shalt not pry!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael remained silent.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Will you be forgiving the poor country manners of an Irishman?\'94\loch\f0  Herity asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John stared at Herity. Jock had as much as said Herity had been in the\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Provos. \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re all sorts of manners in our world,\'94\loch\f0 
\hich\f0  John said. \'93\loch\f0 As Father Michael would say, you can forgive anything that doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t cut the life out of you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A man of wit,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said, but his voice was bitter.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael shifted position\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 , rubbing his hands in front of him. He looked first at Herity and then at John. \'93\loch\f0 You don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
t know about our Joseph Herity, John.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Be still, Priest,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll not be still, Joseph.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael shook his head. \'93\loch\f0 Our Joseph was going to\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 be an important man in this land. He studied the law, did Joseph Herity. There was them that said he might be first among us someday.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That was a long time ago and it came to nothing,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What changed you, Joseph?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael ask\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 All the lying and the cheating! And you there with the worst of \hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 em, Michael Flannery.\'94\loch\f0  Herity put a companionable hand on John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
\hich\f0 s arm. \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s a cold floor but a dry one, John. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll watch until midnight and then you can stand awake until dawn. Best\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 we start early and go overland instead of the road. There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s trails, y\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  know.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Hunted men always learn where the trails are,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And they learn to avoid men who talk too much,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said. He took up his machine gun, slipped \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
his poncho over his head and looked distastefully at the wet cap on the floor. Rain no longer beat against the roof. He put the cap on the hearth near the fire and straightened, stretching. The machine gun made a sharp outline under the poncho as he moved
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Keep the fire,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll do me watching from outside.\'94\loch\f0 
 With that, he crossed to the door and let himself out.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 We had grand hopes for him once,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said. Using his pack as a pillow, he lay down with his feet toward the orange glow \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 of the peat fire.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The boy lay curled up like a hedgehog, his head in the anorak, a dark mound at a corner of the fireplace.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John followed the priest\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s example, his thoughts filled with Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s sharp questioning. You don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t reminisce. The man was 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
carefully observant. John began reviewing their conversations, the things they said as they walked. Nothing casual came from Herity. John realized belatedly that the man was a trained interrogator, getting his answers from the reactions he saw as much as 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 f\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 rom the words he heard. He studied the law. The rough manners, the country accent \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 part of an elaborate pose. Herity went deep. John fell asleep wondering what he might have revealed to that watchful man.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Much later, John awoke thinking he had heard \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
a strange sound. He groped for the machine gun on the floor beside his pack, felt the cold metal. He took a deep breath, smelling the close odors of themselves in the confined space \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 an attar of human sweat distilled from their long tramp and the fatigue\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 that sent them sprawling into sleep whenever they could. He sat up in the darkness and shifted the machine gun to his lap.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A snort nearby. Snoring.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The fire was out.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The room was a black confinement that focused on a sudden sound of scratchi\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ng. A match flared and John looked into Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s face less than a meter away.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re awake,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. The match went out. \'93\loch\f0 You can keep watch from inside, John, should you prefer. There\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 \hich\f0 s not a sign of pursuit for more than a mile out.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  stood. There was starlight visible out the window.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s turned cold, it has,\'94\loch\f0  Herity whispered.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John heard him stretching out on the floor, the little movements of trying to find a comfortable position. Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s breathing deepened, became slow \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 and even.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The machine gun was a cold weight in John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s hands. Why had Herity let him have this dangerous weapon? It could kill the three sleeping figures in seconds.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John went to a window and stared out into the starlit night, the pale silver of a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 winter meadow laid out against the dark backdrop of trees. He stood there, shifting occasionally from one foot to the other, thinking about this strange man, Joseph Herity.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The lying and the cheating.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity had been an idealist. He no longer wa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 s an idealist. Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s question lay in John\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s awareness: What changed you, Joseph? Change\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  change\'85
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John Roe O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill had been changed. No question about what did it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Circumstances.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      In time, the sky lightened to the east and a red-ora\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
nge sun came over the treetops. It was a perfect Japanese Rising Sun for a moment, spokes radiating upward through a mist. Bird sounds came from the ring of trees beyond the meadow. The growing light cast a flush over the landscape, throwing into relief a
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 dark track of crushed grass leading off through the overgrown meadow.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity spoke from the floor behind him. \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s no church bells to waken us anymore.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Father Michael coughed and there was a stirring from him as he sat up. \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll be bells\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  again, Joseph.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Only to send their alarms over the towns and the countryside. Your Church is dead, Priest, just as dead as all the women.\'94
