\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      On the narrow trails and the back roads, across the bogs and through dank tree-filled hills, twisting and turning over the heights, sometimes \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
camping cold, sometimes snug in abandoned cottages, Herity led his party toward Dublin. They were eighteen days reaching the Wicklow foothills, another nine days circling around to come in from the northeast where they were not expected. And hardly a soul
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 to be seen in the entire passage.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      To John, the trip became a constant careful sparring with Herity. The most casual conversation could be dangerous. One afternoon, they had passed a leaning signboard with one word on it: Garretstown. It had been cold 
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 with a wet wind whipping over the hills, and John had longed for something warmer than the sweater.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s things done for no reason in this land,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said suddenly, glancing sidelong at John. Both of them were heavily whiskered now, John\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 s bald\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  head a veined contrast.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What things?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Like slaughtering the hounds of the Kildare Hunt. It was a mean thing, taking out on dumb animals the misery caused by irresponsible humans.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Father Michael spoke from behind them. \'93\loch\f0 The Hu\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 nt was an English thing.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I was there,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 And maybe there was a reason as you say, Priest. Provocation \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 the Hunt crowd not understanding how easy it is to expose the devil in your neighbor.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John nodded, submitting to an urge to pro\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 d at Herity. \'93\loch\f0 The way someone provoked O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity did not rise to this bait, but he walked silently for a time. Father Michael moved up beside them as they came out onto a narrow farm road of unpaved dirt. The boy could be heard trailing along b
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ehind.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve thought the same thing!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. He looked full at John with an expression of amazement on his long face. \'93\loch\f0 
\hich\f0 The foolishness of people is beyond understanding.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Like wanting to resume the Dublin Horse Show?\'94\loch\f0  Herity asked,\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 his voice rilled with slyness. He, too, looked at John, the men walking along, one on each side of John, both looking at him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That was trying to bring back the good things,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said, but he kept his attention on John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Business as u\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 sual!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, looking ahead. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
As though nothing had happened to make it obscene. Tell us about it, Father. You was there.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They plodded along in silence for almost fifty paces before Father Michael responded. In that time, he took his gaze off J\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ohn and stared at the ground in front of him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It was raining a bit,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 
We came on it after the mob had mostly gone. I saw some of the last of them coming away. Carrying boots, some of them were. And bits of clothing. I saw one man\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 with a fine coat over one arm and bloody jodhpurs over the other, a great grin on his face.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice was low and remote, as though he recounted something seen in a foreign land, a wonder from some heathen place and not an event from ci\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
vilized Ireland.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The four walkers were in a dip in the road now, a short bridge visible at the bottom and a boggy stream winding its way through reeds under the bridge.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That mob, they didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t seem ashamed of what they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d done,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Ahhh,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s anger here just waiting for something to strike.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 There was bodies all over the grounds,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Men\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  dead horses\'85\loch\f0 
 gore. No way to tell Catholic from another. They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d taken away all the crosses for t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 heir metal. Not even a ring left. Fingers cut off to get them. I knelt in the mud and prayed.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But who did it?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A mob,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked at Father Michael, fascinated. He pictured the priest coming on that scene, starin\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 g down at bodies of Horse Show officials and audience. Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s simple words conjured a vision.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They even took most of the boots and stockings,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Boots and stockings. Why did they do that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The vision of bare feet ou\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
tstretched in that muddy carnage like a final gesture of lost humanity stirred John oddly. He felt deeply moved, far beyond the brutal facts being recounted in Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s dull voice. Something besides life had gone out of Ireland with those deaths, \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 J\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ohn thought. He even felt an absence of glee from O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within. Interest, yes \hich\f0 
\endash \loch\f0  fascinated interest, but no particular joy. Perhaps it was satisfaction, O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill-Within felt\'85\loch\f0  a feeling of contentment.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John realized then that there was a deep and tell\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ing difference between happiness and contentment. O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Neill-Within might be content with what had been wrought even while it brought him no happiness.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 How do you feel about this, John?\'94\loch\f0  Herity asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It brings me no joy,\'94\loch\f0  John said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 A black\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  day,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Would you listen to him now?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity asked. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
The only Catholics there was the hostlers and the grooms, the hard-working folk. A pack of Protestant landlords answered for their misdeeds and the priest is upset.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Michael spoke more strongly. \'93\loch\f0 They were murdered! Slaughtered like animals \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  with knives, clubs, pitchforks and bare hands. There wasn
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t a shot fired.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Herity looked at John. \'93\loch\f0 Does this give you any idea atall, atall, what might happen should the Mad\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 man O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill appear in our midst?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John sensed O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within, silently watchful.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 All those deaths and no good reason,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. \'93\loch\f0 Oh, there was reason, but I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ll agree with the priest that it was better not done.\'94\loch\f0  Herity leaned across John to \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 address Father Michael. \'93\loch\f0 But you were fascinated by all that death, weren\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
t you, Priest? A good reason to pray with your knees in the mud.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael plodded along with his gaze directed downward. He shuddered.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John glanced at the priest, se\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 nsing the darting accuracy of Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s remark. Yes, Father Michael shared his Church\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s love-hate relationship with death. It was his source of power as a priest, but the man-within could not be denied, either. No more could O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within. Death was the u\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
timate failure, the human weakness that went beyond illusion into illusion, that intervention whose absolute sway could not be avoided.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity saw concealed things!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s educational it is,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 listening to the voice of a man when you \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
cannot see his face.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Again, he leaned forward to peer across John at the priest. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
I listened to you, Michael Flannery. You telling about that slaughter and not a sign to say you see at last why I spit on your Church!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael did not respond.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     Herity grinned and returned his attention to the road ahead of them. The boy could be heard behind them throwing a rock into the bushes. They had topped the rise beyond the stream now and looked down a long hill where the road entered a thick barrier
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 of evergreens.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You see, Priest,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 what is most difficult is to be abandoned by God. He left me. I did not leave Him. They have taken away my religion!
\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s eyes glistened with unshed tears. He thought: }{\i\dbch\af11\insrsid3359690 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 Oh, yes, Joseph H\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
erity, I understand about that. I know all the psychological things they taught in the seminary. You would say the Church is my substitute for sex. It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s the love I could never find from a woman. Oh, yes, I understand you. It
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s a new Church you think we ha\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 v\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e and not a woman for any of us}{\dbch\af11\insrsid3359690 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Without knowing why, Father Michael felt strength entering him from Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s words.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Thank you, Joseph,\'94\loch\f0  he said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Thank me? What is this you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re saying?\'94\loch\f0  Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice was filled with outrage.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I though\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 t I was alone,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 I see that I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m not. For that, I thank you.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Crab the man!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said. He fell into angry silence, replaced presently by a sly smile. \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re confused, Priest,\'94
\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s none of us together.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 saw the look of amusement on Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s face. And Father Michael\'85\loch\f0  confusion? Herity obviously took malicious enjoyment from another\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 s confusion. Did he enjoy Ireland\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s confusion as well? No\'85\loch\f0  that went contrary to Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s Cause. The plague had upset the unt\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 o
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 uchable. Recognizing this, John realized with an abrupt shock of awareness that he had the key to Herity, the thing that would undo the man.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Destroy his belief in his Cause!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      But that was the very thing Herity was trying to do to Father Michael. H\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ow could that be a weakness in Herity and\'85\loch\f0  yes, a strength in Father Michael?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re your politics, Joseph?\'94\loch\f0  John asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Me politics?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He grinned. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m a liberal, I am. Always was.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a godless Marxist,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Bet\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ter than a godless priest,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 John, d\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 you know about the war of indefinite duration?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Close your fly trap, Michael Flannery,\'94\loch\f0  Herity said, his voice even and venomous.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Never heard of it,\'94\loch\f0  John said. He sen\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 sed a poised stillness in Herity.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s the Proves,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said. He returned Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s black look with a smile. \'93\loch\f0 
Prevent any settlement, kill the ones who\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d compromise, terrify the peacemakers, prevent any solution. Give the people only war \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 and violence, death and terror until they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
re so sick of it they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll accept anything in its place, even the godless Marxists.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll recall,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Herity said, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 that this priest mourned the Prod landlords at the Dublin Horse Show. The greedy capitalists!
\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They were greedy, right enough,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael said. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll grant you that. It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s greed that drives the conservatives. But it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s envy driving the liberals. And these Marxists\'85\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he hooked a disdainful thumb at Herity \'93\loch\f0 . . . all they want is to sit in t
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 e seats of the mighty and lord it over everyone else. The intellectual aristocrats!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John heard a new strength in Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice. The man apparently possessed powerful roots and he had found them. He might be beset by doubts, but the strength \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
he gained by struggling against his doubts accumulated. It grew day by day.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Now that I know how to pray for you, I shall pray for you, Joseph Herity,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John looked from one man to the other, sensing the deep currents between \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      A malicious grin came over Herity\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s mouth but did not touch his eyes. He patted the machine gun on its strap at his chest. \'93\loch\f0 Here\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s me soul, Priest. Pray for this.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a demon loose in our land, Joseph,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herit\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 y sobered. A wild look entered his eyes. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A demon is it?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A demon,\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael repeated.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Still with that sober look, Herity said: \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Mercie secure ye all, and keep the Goblin from ye, while ye sleep.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  His wolfish grin returned. \'93\loch\f0 The words of R
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 obert Herrick, Priest. Y\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0  see the advantages in a classical education?\'94
