\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Rupert Stonar, political watchdog on Huddersfield\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s plague research, stood directly under a spotlight in Hupp\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s working lab. Light glistened off glassware on the table beside him; it picked out lines of red in his unruly sandy hair. His e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 xpression had been carved in rock.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It was past midnight but Hupp did not know how much past. He had left his watch on his bedside table when answering the summons and had not been given time enough even to glance at it. A tough Royal Marine, someone H
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 upp had never seen before, had escorted him to the lab and left him about a pace from Stonar. There was no one else in the room. Hupp felt at a disadvantage in a bathrobe.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      As the Royal Marine left, Stonar said: \'93\loch\f0 Post a guard and let no one else in her\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 e.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes, sir!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Hupp decided he did not like the disdainful stare in Stonar\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s pale blue eyes. There had been a great many military types around in the halls and on the grounds \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 and Hupp did not like that, either, but he kept his feelings to hims\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 elf.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What is happening?\'94\loch\f0  Hupp asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You are at a critical stage in your researches,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Stonar said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 How critical?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      How had Stonar found out? Hupp wondered. He said: \'93\loch\f0 Wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t it be better if you talked to Wycombe-Finch or Doctor Beckett?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why do you not suggest I talk to Doctor Ruckerman? After all, has he not recently made a thorough study of the work at this facility?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      So Stonar also knew what Ruckerman had brought, Hupp realized. This could get sticky. He said: \'93\loch\f0 Ruckerman woul\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 d be a good choice. Where is he?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll be brought to me when I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m ready for him.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But why me?\'94\loch\f0  Hupp asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I must be certain to get the truth. Your family is closer and more accessible to us. Consequences of a lie would be extremely painf\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ul to you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      All of this was uttered in a flat monotone, knotting Hupp\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s stomach with fear. Genine! The boys! Hupp knew only too well how precarious was their safety in the Dordogne Reserve.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What have you achieved?\'94\loch\f0  Stonar asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We are app\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 roaching a precise biochemical description of the plague,\'94\loch\f0  Hupp said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Would you stake your life on that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes.\'94\loch\f0  Hupp stared back at Stonar, thinking how appropriate was the man\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s nickname: Stoney. Those eyes had been chipped from sapphire.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Does this mean that presently you will be able to reproduce the plague?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Or an\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  antidote.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Convince me.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Hupp glanced down the length of his cluttered lab. Not a chair in sight. This was not the place he would have chosen for an intervie\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 w \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 too much evidence of his own volatility.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s quite complex,\'94\loch\f0  Hupp said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Simplify it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Hupp groped in his robe pocket for his glasses, anything for a prop. The Royal Marine had not allowed him time to dress and now Hupp remembered that\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 his glasses were with his watch on the bedside table. His feet were cold, protected only by slippers from the hard floor.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The intertwining helix bends back and forth on itself,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Hupp said. \'93\loch\f0 You see this, for example, in the gene for botulinus or cho\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
\hich\f0 lera toxin, and even for ordinary enteric organisms.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Enteric?\'94\loch\f0  Stonar asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Things that can live in the small intestine.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Are you saying O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill could have changed an ordinary organism into something like cholera?\'94
