\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Who are you, John Garrech O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Donnell?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny asked. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Who are you, really?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve told you,\'94\loch\f0  John gasped. The words hur\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 t his throat.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Did you tell the priest, as well?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John hunched his shoulders, leaning forward. The pain in his chest and throat demanded relief.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve found his fingerprints and dental charts in the States,\'94\loch\f0  Doheny said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Whose\'85\'94\loch\f0  It \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 was all John could speak.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s, of course. They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re playing it cagey, the bastards, but we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ll have them in time. What will those fingerprints and dental charts show us, John?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John shook his head from side to side, once more mute. He could n\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ot feel O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill-Within. He could only feel a great emptiness there.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re a queer specimen and that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s no mistake,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Do you have real feelings?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John stared back at Doheny, locked in place by those questioning eyes.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re that\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  close to victory,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That close.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 He held up thumb and forefinger of his right hand, a tiny gap between them. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And now this!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      John managed a whisper. \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s\'85\loch\f0 \hich\f0  happening?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The thing that always destroys us,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 Victory. We\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
