\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      For Kate O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Gara Browder, the flight from the research facility was a nightmare from beginning to end. Doheny had given them little ti\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
me to think or question his decision.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s for your own safety.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But where are we going?\'94\loch\f0  Stephen had asked. He had peered out at Doheny through the same small port where Father Michael Flannery had stood the previous morning to perform the mar
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 riage ceremony.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 To Dundalk for now,\'94\loch\f0  Doheny said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Even as he spoke, there had been no turning back. It had begun with the stopping of the air pumps, that constant reassuring noise that told them the chamber\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s pressure was higher than the pressur
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e outside, that nothing of the plague might creep into this sanctuary. They had lived with the sound so long by then that they no longer noticed it, but the absence!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Stephen! The air pumps have stopped!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      He leaped to his feet and dashed to the m\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ain porthole, which commanded a view of the enclosing area outside and some of the equipment.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What do you see?\'94\loch\f0  she demanded, pressing close behind him. A sense of engulfing terror gripped her. Please, God! Not now.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s no one out there,\'94\loch\f0  S\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 tephen said. He went to the communications panel and thumbed the microphone switch. \'93
\loch\f0 Hi, out there. What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s going on?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      There was no response.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      They heard it then, many footsteps, the sound curiously localized by the speaker above the port. There wa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a dragging noise with the sound of footsteps\'85\loch\f0 
 heavy dragging and the sound of metal scraping on stones.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s Doheny,\'94\loch\f0  Stephen said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      She squeezed in beside Stephen to peer out at Doheny. He looked flushed. His fuzzy hair was more disarrayed \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 than usual. Doheny took up the outside phone.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s all right. The pump will not be off long,\'94\loch\f0  he said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 But what\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s happening?\'94\loch\f0  Stephen demanded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      That was when Doheny said they were being moved for their own safety, being taken to Dundalk. W\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 hy Dundalk? Kate wondered.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Be sure to take your supply of the antiseptic in with you,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny said. \'93\loch\f0 And that rope you used for a safety line when we moved you from the barn \hich\f0 
\endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  rig that again. You may be tossed about a bit.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doheny\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s instructions\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 were uttered in an intense monotone that they had never before heard from him. They were to take everything they thought they would need and stow it securely in the original chamber from Peard\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s barn. Stephen was to paint antiseptic around the tank\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s ent\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 r\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
y port. And hurry! Men with cutting torches were waiting to burn away the metal juncture between the original tank and the one built here.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We can\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t move both of them,\'94\loch\f0  Doheny explained.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But why are we doing this?\'94\loch\f0  Stephen persisted.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Becau\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 se I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve convinced some friends in the army that we cannot keep Kate alive here!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Where\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s Adrian?\'94\loch\f0  Stephen asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s under guard in his quarters. Adrian\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s joined the enemy. Keep your pistol with you, Stephen. Kevin O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 s coming and there\loch\af0\dbch\af11\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s no stopping him. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s insane and he wants Kate.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But why Dundalk?\'94\loch\f0  Kate asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Because we hope to get you completely out of Ireland. We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve enough of the army and others loyal to us that we can get you safely to Dundalk. From there\'85\'94
\loch\f0  Doheny b\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 roke off.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Where?\'94\loch\f0  Stephen demanded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 To England, we hope. Everything depends on Barrier Command.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Doheny returned to his original instructions then. \'93\loch\f0 
And it would not hurt to drench a sheet with the antiseptic. Put it over the inside of the acce\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ss port after you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve closed and sealed it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The air pressure,\'94\loch\f0  Stephen said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll have a pump going again soon as we put you onto the lorry. You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
ll have positive pressure again. Best get into the little chamber as rapidly as you can.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Nyl\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
an Gunn, commander of the Killaloe guard, had come down then to take over from Doheny, telling the latter he was needed in communications. Gunn was a slender, dark Galway man with slightly bowed legs and a face with small features. He had been a commander
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 in the constabulary before the plague.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t worry, lass,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he told Kate. \'93\loch\f0 We\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll not let the mad O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell have y\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 .\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Moone had been right behind him \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 to say goodbye.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Trust Fin Doheny and Nylan here,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll save you. And don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
\hich\f0 ave any more truck with Adrian Peard!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What has Adrian done?\'94\loch\f0  Stephen asked. He felt that the ground was being cut away from beneath him. Adrian betraying them? How? What had he done?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve had a leetle microphone in the bastard\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s office for mon\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ths now,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Moone said. \'93
\loch\f0 He was too slick for me! Sure enough, he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s unlocked the door for Kevin O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Donnell to come and lord it over us.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Stephen had heard the stories of Kevin O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Donnell and the Beach Boys. He glanced at Kate.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Do what Nylan tells yo\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 u,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Moone said. \'93\loch\f0 Goodbye, Katie. Have a brave child even if y\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 are married.\'94\loch\f0  Chuckling, he left them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It was all mad movement then, loud conversations and the sound of heavy equipment outside, the outer wall being breached. She and Stephen entered the\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 small chamber finally and Stephen sealed the inner port, drenched a sheet with antiseptic and fastened it over the port. The small space reeked with the acrid smell of the antiseptic.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Kate sat close to Stephen on the bed, clutching him tightly when s\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
he heard the burners cutting away the outer chamber, even tighter when the cables went around their container and it swung free to settle with a thump onto an unsteady support on the lorry. The lashing cables rang against the chamber\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 s steel when they wer\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 dropped into place and tightened. The end port gave them a view of the new opening through the bricks that had been put there such a short time ago to enclose their containers.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The sound of the compressor returned, soothing them somewhat. They could \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 hear the generator motor chugging loudly behind them near the lorry\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s cab.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The lorry began to move so gently that they did not feel it at first, then they saw the opening into the castle receding and felt a wheel lurch into a rut. There was the sound \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
of other vehicles, several of them. Stephen peered outside. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A lot of armored cars,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Must be ten or twelve of them.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Nylan Gunn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s voice came to them then from the little emergency speaker near the head of the bed. \'93\loch\f0 Everything all right in th\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ere?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Stephen found the microphone and keyed it. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It seems to be okay. How long will we be like this?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 No telling, lad. But I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m up here with the driver. Sing out if you need me.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Stephen looked at Kate. She appeared pale and her forehead wa\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 s deeply furrowed. \'93\loch\f0 Why don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t you stretch out and try to sleep, darling?\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I couldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t sleep!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 But you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d be safer if you were on the mattress there.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 No, I wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t. This is not safe.\'94\loch\f0  She closed her eyes. The baby felt so heavy in her abdo\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
