\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Meet Alex Coleman,\'94\loch\f0  Kevin said\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 . \'93\loch\f0 Pickled in whiskey at last and that his dream of paradise, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
m sure.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kevin focused a wide-eyed stare on John, motioning for Doheny to stand aside. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 This was the traitor whose warning let Fin here spirit away from us the pride of Ireland.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Doheny s\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 aid: \'93\loch\f0 Kevin, you \hich\f0 \endash \'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t interrupt! You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re here under sufferance and only so long as you live up to our agreement!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Six men came out from the stacks then at Kevin\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s signal and took seats in the row of chairs, seating themselves with a noisy scr\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
aping of the wooden legs on the floor, coughs and low-voiced comments.
