 He tapped the bottle beside him. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But the triumvirate is present and the trial will proceed.\'94\loch\f0  Kevin let his gaze wander over the others in the room, settling at \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 last on Herity. \'93
\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s time, Joseph.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Herity put his bottle aside gently and lifted a sheet of paper from the stack on the table. He read from it, glancing occasionally at John.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We say first that you, prisoner, are John Roe O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill. We say you ar\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
e the author of the plague which has outraged our poor land and much of the world besides, making an exception for the British and the heathens to whom it was a just punishment. We say you had no cause to harm us in this cowardly fashion. And how do you p
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ead, John Roe O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      John stared at the head in the bottle. It was speaking to him in the voice of O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 Neill! \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What was my crime?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  it asked. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
