\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Strange, the rumors and stories coming out of Ireland about O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill. He was seen here; he was seen there; but never a confirmation. \hich\f0 \lquote \loch\f0 Twas said that people were putting
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 out food and drink for him the way they had once done for the Little People. Ahhh, there was no accounting for Irish behavior. Look at the hero they were making of Brann McCrae and him with twenty-six of those young girls pregnant!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 But he saved almo\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 st fifty Irish women!\'94\loch\f0 
 they were saying. Saved! What good was it saving their flesh if their souls were lost? It was not as though McCrae were the only one who had saved women from the plague. They were saying it would be generations before all the storie
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0  were told of how women had been secreted and protected by their clever men. Not enough saved, though. But efforts would be made to bring them all back to God\'85\loch\f0 
 even the poor girls at McCrae\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s chateau. It had not been their doing. They had been caught by t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e troubled times.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
     As he neared the Administration Building, where Kate and her husband were quartered, Father Michael saw the usual long line of men waiting to be threaded past the viewing window where Kate could be seen. Just to see a woman was a mag
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 netic thing, so powerful that the authorities could not deny the demands. Too dangerous, they said. And what harm did it do?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It harms Kate, Father Michael thought. Just showing herself was bringing about changes in the woman that Father Michael feared\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 . Was this the thing Doheny had warned against?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael made his way past the waiting men, hearing the bits of conversations:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 She\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a pretty thing, I hear.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And with a baby at her breast.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael saw resentment in the f\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
aces of the men he passed. They knew he had a right to push ahead, but there was a jealous awareness here that he could go in and talk to Kate, even touch her.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      The line of men wound in a long serpentine up the stairs inside the building. Father Michae\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
l ignored the stairs and went to the lift at the center of the long corridor. The guard at the lift opened the door for Father Michael and punched the button for the top floor.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Birney Cavanagh was waiting outside the lift as Father Michael emer\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ged on the top floor. There was no getting around the man and Father Michael was forced to stop.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Ahh, there you are, Father Michael. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve been waiting for you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Where had the Brits found this priest? Father Michael wondered. Oh, Cavanagh was a C\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
atholic priest, right enough. That had been confirmed. But he had been too long with the Gall. He even spoke with the accents of an Old Etonian.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What is it you want?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Father Michael demanded. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Just a word or two, Father.\'94\loch\f0  Cavanagh took Father Michael\loch\af0\dbch\af11\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 s arm and almost forced him into a corner beyond the lift.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael stared down at the other priest. Cavanagh was a cherubic little man with pale cheeks. There was an insecurity in his blue eyes, which seemed always to be looking for an avenue \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
of escape. Did he ever comb that gray hair? Father Michael wondered. It always seemed to have just come through a whirlwind.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A good Irishman,\'94\loch\f0  he claimed to be. And wasn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t he out of St. Patrick\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s College, Maynooth, the same as Father Michael?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Ha\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 d he gone through the troubles there? Father Michael had inquired, seeking to trap the man in a lie.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No. I was sent out ten years before.\'94\loch\f0  And that had proved to be true enough.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      But Cavanagh was seeing Kate and talking to her. And Father Michael\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 did not like the mood of the woman when Cavanagh had gone. The man was thick with the papal envoy who had come over from Philadelphia, too, and Father Michael did not like what he heard about that. There was talk of an accommodation with \'93\loch\f0 
the demands of \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 hese changing times.\'94\loch\f0 
 Father Michael knew what that meant: backsliding! Nothing good would come of it. There might even be a new schism. How could anyone respect a Catholic Church with its administrative seat in America? Things would not get back to norma
\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  until Rome was restored.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You cannot go in to Kate just now,\'94\loch\f0  Father Cavanagh was saying, his eyes avoiding Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
She has an important visitor.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Who is it now?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 The admiral over all the Barrier Command, the one who saved her \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 by permitting the channel passage.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 God saved her!\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael protested.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Of that there is no doubt,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Cavanagh agreed. \'93\loch\f0 But it was the admiral\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s command that gave her passage.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The channel would have parted if God had wanted it,\'94\loch\f0  Fath\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 er Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I agree,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Cavanagh said, \'93\loch\f0 but the admiral has his powers and we cannot disturb him just now. It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s for her own good, I assure you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why is he seeing her?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael demanded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 As to that, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m not at liberty to say.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0   \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0    Father Michael put down a surge of anger. He knew Cavanagh sensed it, because the man released Father Michael\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s arm and stepped back defensively.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What is happening in there?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael asked, keeping his voice under careful control.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 The\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 re\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s guards on the door and you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll not be permitted to enter,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Cavanagh said. \'93
\loch\f0 I promise you, there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s no harm coming to her.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael sensed truth in Cavanagh\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s words and wondered if it would be right to force the issue. I am an envoy of the Ir\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
ish state! But that had its strictures, too. An envoy must behave with proper decorum. He sensed Doheny\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s fears coming true. That silly woman was famous all over the world. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 The Woman in the Tank!\'94
\loch\f0  Something about her had caught the public fancy. It was t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 e press doing it, of course! All of those sensational stories. And the baby being born during the storm of the channel crossing.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 When will I be permitted to see her?\'94\loch\f0  Father Michael asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Perhaps this afternoon sometime. Would you care to wait\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  in my quarters, Father. They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve given me digs just down the corridor here.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Father Michael felt a hollow hardness in his stomach. Something bad was happening and he was to be kept out of it. Well, he would fight! Before he could speak, though, three \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
armed naval officers came down the corridor, their attention on him. Father Michael knew then that he was to be a prisoner and these were his guards.
