\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Beckett had recounted this to General Monk during the first part of the flight, watching the amusement and speculation in the man\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s eyes. How was a possible President of the United States taking to such an insight?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      This was one cow who was\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  going to be bullish, Beckett thought. After Monk left him alone, Beckett began framing a campaign speech.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 We need a scientist in the White House. We need someone who knows the real dangers facing our world. We need someone capable of assessing the t\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
rue nature of what our scientific laboratories produce.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Yes \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  give them the idea that the plague might not have occurred had there been a scientist President. That would do it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A woman for every man!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      It was a good slogan and might be an a\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ttainable goal. The idea carried dangerous undertones of ownership, though. Were women to be hostages to a human future?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Hupp had been absolutely right about one thing: They need us, damn them!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      There was mounting evidence that O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill had created\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
 more than he knew in that crude laboratory of his. Now that people were once more moving about, crossing the old borders and the new ones, diseases never before observed were beginning to crop up. O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
Neill had probably been a walking factory of infections\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 .\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  They could trace his path by where the new diseases were appearing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      God! One man had done this.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0      Was O\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 Neill still wandering insane in Ireland? It was possible. A form of that primitive respect for madness had come over the Irish. They were perfe\hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 
